name: Cozy room in Lisdoonvarna - near Cliffs of Moher
description:
Enjoy a stay in your private garden-view room with your own bathroom! It is a modern house with pubs, restaurants, a café & bus stop in easy walking distance. From here, you can explore the Atlantic coast, the Aran Islands, the Burren, the Cliffs of Moher & much more!

From the 1st May to 31 August 2025, a free shuttle bus will bring you to locations on the coast and in the Burren National Park. You'll even get free admission to the Cliffs with that bus ticket!
neighborhood_overview:
I live in a quiet neighbourhood which is nonetheless very close to the square and all the shops, pubs, restaurants and the café. Actually you can see the square from my house. At the same time, going the other way, there is a lovely valley where you can walk, or reach the sea in just 10 minutes by car. The world-famous Cliffs of Moher are only a 20 min drive away, and the Burren (an amazing limestone area) are very close, too.
You can also do day trips to the Aran Islands, as the ferries to the islands go from Doolin, a 15 min drive away.

There are two beaches in the area - Fanore Beach to the north and Lahinch to the south.

FESTIVALS:

These are some of the festivals taking place in the area. Please search for them for more details, I'm not allowed to post website addresses.

Burren in Bloom Festival - annual, May
Burren Slow Food Festival - annual, May
Burren Rocks!
Doolin Folk Festival - annual, June
Doolin Craft B
host_about: I'm originally from Germany and speak German, French and English. I welcome international visitors and have an extensive knowledge of the local area which I'm happy to share with you in any of the above languages! Some of my hobbies are photography and geocaching.

name: Compass Hill House - Harbour views
description:
An eclectic Georgian townhouse over 3 storeys. Available for longer stays (fortnight or more) and up to six months lease.

Compass Hill has commanding views over the harbour and across to Scilly and the Bulman. There's lots of space inside and out to allow your head to breathe. It is perfect for families.

Rentals of two weeks or more must take up the bills; electricity, tv internet, and any oil needed for the AGA range.

Take a virtual tour: search for "Compass Hill House" on an online map...
neighborhood_overview: Kinsale is a treat! It's not like any other place in Ireland, situated as it is on a safe harbour, it was strategically important in the late 1700's,  but has a naval history stretching further back in time. It is a relatively deep basin, surrounded on three sides by steeply sloping hills. The town then, is like an amphitheatre. All of the business activities, fun and entertainment happen down by the quays, and everyone lives up the hills. Compass Hill is worth a long walk around, it commands the most spectacular views over the inlet and harbour. Stroll - or roll - into the town to take in the plentiful nightlife, with music and craic in most pubs and bars, fine dining options in the many restaurants. For families, there is plenty to occupy the daylight hours. The Outdoor Activity Centre is just 50m from the front door, and there are a great many options for water sports, sailing, and mucking about in boats. Ask us for more info...
host_about:
I am an artist living and working between Dublin and Italy. I make original print (if this needs explaining, visit my website, a quick search on my name will get it for you).

This house in Kinsale town is a fabulous Georgian period three storey townhouse that is our escape from the Dublin.

Feel free to contact us at any time, we try very hard to respond to requests quickly.

Marie-Louise Martin & Marcus Casey

name: Cosy Comfortable Irish Cottage  1 Double Bed
description:
Our Cottage is a charming light filled cottage in the vibrant district of Dundrum this area was noted in days gone by as a Spa resort ,
We have a terrific transport network locally ,the Luas a fast tram service in Dundrum will bring you to the city centre in 13 mins, the 14 bus is 2 mins from us ,
The 750 Dublin Coach Bus from the Airport stops locally & is 12 mins walk
There are loads of restaurants ,bars ,& shops within walking distance from our place ,
neighborhood_overview:
I love Dundrum and its surrounding areas ,
There is a huge Shopping Mall 10 mins walk from here with an enormous array of restaurants ranging from Jamie Oliver's to Mexican ,Thai Tapas Bars ,Italian there are a great variety of shops ,Harvey Nicholls ,Michael Kors ,,Hollister & some good pubs & restaurants in our village Churchtown..which is just down the road ,
There are great transport links ,great access to everywhere we are very near the city 4 miles away ,the mountains are about 8 miles away and the sea is 4 miles , the 750 Dublin Coach bus comes from the Airport to Dundrum village 10 mins walk from here ,what's not to like about that !

There are some lovely villages nearby ,Enniskerry is a lovely little village at the foot of the Dublin mountains & has a beautiful Palladian mansion & gardens worth visiting ,there is a bus locally that will take you there
Ranelagh is noted as a foodie village its about 2 miles from here & has some really good rest

name: Peaceful cottage central to places of interest
description:
A charming cottage which is located along the picturesque East Clare walking trail and only a 45 minute drive to the spectacular 'Burren' National Park
30 minute drive to Lough Derg
25 minutes to Ennis
10 minutes from 2 nearby villages
Shannon Airport 45 minutes
Wild Atlantic Way and Galway/Limerick cities are within an hour's reach.

A home from home, this small but spasious selfcatering cottage has a well equipped kitchen with a full sized cooker and condiments for meal preparation.
neighborhood_overview:
DRUID COTTAGE gets its name from the area 'Glendree' which means Glen of kings and some say, Glen of druids or magic.
Situated on a scenic hillside between the villages of Feakle and Tulla luckily on the East Clare walking trail and not far from Lough Derg to the east and the Wild Atlantic way to the west. We are also situated half way between the two towns of Ennis and Gort for big shops, museums and a Cathedral.
Feakle is famous for the Traditional music festival and the whole area is inhabited by friendly welcoming farmers, artists and healers.
A short walk from the cottage there is a nearby family producing whole organic fresh milk, cheese, eggs and seasonal vegetables for sale.
host_about:
Born in Dublin Ireland with wanderlust I experienced some years of world travel, eventually putting roots in Clare to raise my family and  immerse myself in the art of textiles, nature and a slower outdoor pace of life. 
 I still travel, enjoy meeting people and guests but can also allow them their space by responding to any questions by message on Airbnb or What's App :)

 "Look into nature and you will understand everything" Albert Einstein

name: KERRY - Heritage Town of Listowel
description:
Great property in Kerry where you will be assured of a warm Irish Welcome from Betty and John.

This is a holiday destination - NO WORK CREWS.

Come and enjoy the Kerry craic! (Craic is the Irish word for fun!)

On 3/4 of an acre, the all level accommodation and suitable for persons with limited mobility and wheelchair users. Free WiFi.
neighborhood_overview:
The Heritage Town of Listowel is a place where you can arrive as a tourist and leave as a local!

The property is in a quiet area and only minutes from the town centre and stores, yet with a countryside feel about it.

A petrol station is only a couple of hundred metres from the property and it has a mini-store for basics. You can also have a breakfast there with other take-away eats.
host_about:
John is a former member of the Irish Defence Forces (Army) and Betty is a retired HSE worker.
We love to travel and we particularly love to  meet and greet good people to our county - The Kingdom of Kerry - Heaven's Reflex - call it what you will, you'll never know until you go!

We love promoting all Ireland, our county, our culture, our history, our fabulous scenery, our music, our songs, and our Irish dancing!

We believe that every host should be an ambassador for their country and do their utmost to help guests enjoy their stay by helping them plan their stay even before they arrive and making sure they enjoy their hard-earned vacation.

We want our guests to leave happy, to want to return again to Ireland and to bring their family and friends next time.
.

name: 5.5 miles south of Dublin City :^)
description: A nice place to relax after the bustle of the city; close to the sea + not far from the Dublin Mountains ~ they are really hills. Clean, bright + fresh ~ with a garden to almost hide in.  TWO BEDROOMS + parking.  From Dublin Airport:  Aircoach 700 to 'STILLORGAN' plus 14 min. walk. Excellent, bus route to city ~ c.35 mins + LUAS/tram.  From €88/night for the first two guests ~ whether or not you use one or two rooms.  Extra guests : €35/night - inc. breakfast.  I live on the top floor.
neighborhood_overview: Close to the sea, hill walks and the city - via bus and car. It is a quiet neighborhood and my neighbors are friendly too.
host_about:
I live here on the third floor of my house.  The two bedrooms shown, and bathroom, are for exclusive use of guests, are all on the middle floor.  Kitchen, ground floor loo + garden are for sharing !

I am a freelance photographer + work extensively in the arts.  I am well travelled, both internally + externally, and have worked in 17 countries; including living in Paris (I have reasonable French) + Copenhagen (I have lousy Danish; although I can say strawberries + cream + 815 as that was my work number)  As regards sign language - I know the alphabet - so, I am a bit of a slow communicator on that front.

I am into social issues + sustainable living.

I have a clean bright home with a garden.

My friends are interesting . . . so are my guests, I've discovered.

Any questions just ask.

Books :  'LIFE - An Enigma a Precious Jewel' Daisaku Ikeda; 'Memoires' John McGahern; 'I Put a Spell on You' John Burnside; 'An Empire of the East - Travels in Indonesia' Norman Lewis; 'Shantaram' Gregory David Roberts.

Films :  Kes, Pixote, The Tin Drum, Münich, The English Patient, Withnail and I, My Left Foot, Annie Hall.

Music :  Jonathan Richman and The Modern Lovers, Ruben Gonzalez, Françoise Hardy, Toquiñho, Vinicius de Morais, Mehmet Ozan, Damien Rice, Rory Gallagher, Georgie Fame, Cat Stevens, Burl Ives, JJ Cale, Dory Previn, Ray LaMontagne, Credence Clearwater Revival, Emiliana Torrini, Georges Brassens, Georges Moustaki, Chopin.

Food :  tea & toast, Ovlatine, Marmite, Twiglets, Mediterranian, Middle Eastern, corn fed steak - rare - I'm a part-time vegetarian; curry, nuts/seeds/berries, juices + smoothies.

Airbnb motto :  'Communication is not a one way street !'

General motto : 'It's OK to break the rules if it creates value !'  ß:^)

Please note, as of 1st October 2022, gas and electricity prices have gone up by c.35%.  Some lights on as security are a good idea but a welcoming committee of lights is not required.  Your comprehension is appreciated.  [Never waste time, food or money]

description: A traditional, 200 year old cottage with some modern comforts and many original features. Located on a quiet back road, the cottage is set in private land with a sweeping meadow at the front and many mature trees to all sides. It is about 6 minutes drive from the nearest town (Glenties) and suits those looking for complete tranquility. Good shops, pubs, places to eat in Glenties and nearby Ardara. Stunning mountain and coastal scenery in every direction.
neighborhood_overview: I live in a secluded and private location with complete tranquility, yet am surrounded by very caring and helpful neighbours. Loves people, cats, traditional Irish fiddle music, especially Donegal playing, countryside, fine cooking and food, nature.

name: The Old Cable Historic House c.1866
description: Our Post Code To Find Us V23X862 A Designated Milestone Heritage Site - tracing its origins to the First Transatlantic Telegraph Cable from Ireland to USA in 1866. Situated at the halfway stopping point on the world famous Ring of Kerry the best land and seascapes in Ireland.
neighborhood_overview:
The small seaside village of Waterville has often been referred to as the ’Jewel’ on the famous Ring of Kerry.Nestled on the edge of the Atlantic Ocean, hugging the shores of Lough Currane (famous worldwide for salmon & specimen sea trout) and enjoying a magnificent backdrop of lush, rugged mountains, it is little wonder that Charlie Chaplin fell in love with this idyllic, picturesque location.Chaplin returned to Waterville for many years with his wife Oona and their children, as, according to members of the Chaplin family, Waterville afforded him a tranquil haven where he could enjoy spending time with his family in relative anonymity. Many locals remember him strolling along the seafront promenade which runs along the centre of the village, his privacy always respected.

One of Chaplin’s favourite pursuits while in Waterville was fishing on Lough Currane.

His grandson Julien (a regular visitor to Waterville today) recounts a story of his grandfather having had a
host_about: Enjoy my work - welcoming and taking good care of our Guests,  a great pride of place - something very special about living in a place where people come from all over the World to see and visit Skellig Michael our 6th Century Monastic Settlement , to enjoy our Dark Skies and ever changing land and seascapes, walk along the Seafront promenade - enjoy an ice cream cone and do nothing but to breathe in the space and beauty , we are lucky enough to live here and to ensure all our guests enjoy their experience of all South Kerry has to offer. I enjoy well cooked good food especially our local Seafood - Kerry Lamb and small local produce, Veg and Breads,  also Foreign Cinema , Jazz Music , Radio and Internet, Irish Social History and of course family.

name: Peaceful retreat for 5 - excellent location
description:
This apartment is quiet and peaceful and is a wonderful retreat at the end of a busy day sightseeing.

Excellent location for seeing the city of Dublin which can be reached in 10 minutes by bus or 30 min walk. Bus stops right outside the front door.

Supermarket 3 minute walk, pub/restuarants 10 min walk
Phoenix Park - 8 min walk
Dublin Zoo - 10 min walk
Playground - 10 min walk
Bike hire - 15 min
Airport transfer can be arranged for a fee
Keysafe available for guests arriving late
neighborhood_overview:
This street is a beautifully tree lined street which runs right up the the entrance of the Phoenix Park.
This park is the largest urban park in Europe and houses Dublin Zoo and the presidential home and offices as well as a children's playground. It is a wonderful park to visit and spans over 1750 acres.
The street also has beautiful Victorian red bricked houses all along it which date back to the 18th century so it really is a taste of old Dublin.
There is a major supermarket just 3 minutes walk as well as a pharmacy, bakery, coffee shops, bars, restuarants and many other amenities all within easy walking distance.
host_about: I grew up in the tourist business as my parents ran a hotel in Kildare so I have always wanted to get back into the hosptality industry.  I have owned this house from the early '90's when I returned from New York where I had lived for a number of years.  I have been in the buidling trade for the last 20 years so I thought I would combine the two and refurbish the house and provide rental accommodation in an extremely convenient locations to tourists.

name: Luxury City Center Penthouse - Best Location
description:
City Center Location with Stunning Views. Overlooking Galway Harbor. It features a full length balcony overlooking Galway Bay giving breathtaking views throughout the apartment. A full host of entertainment options. Located in a prestigious location.

Located 150 meters away from the main shopping street of Galway city "Shop Street" while the center of nightlife activity in Galway "The Latin Quarter" is 100 meters away.
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is located 150 meters away from the main shopping street of Galway city with the Town Square a 2 minute walk away. The center of nightlife activity in Galway "The Latin Quarter" is 100 meters away. There are dozens of pubs and restaurants just outside. Connemara is a 15 minute drive away, Salthill and its beautiful beaches a 20 minute walk. The Cliffs of Moher and the Burren are an hours drive away with the central bus & train station within a 2 minute walk of the apartment. Here you can catch a bus or train to all the tourist attractions and cities of Ireland so it
can be the perfect base for your Ireland holiday. Just about every part of the country can be got to within 2-3 hrs from here.

Dublin may be the official capital of Ireland but there is no doubt about the cultural capital of Ireland, Galway. Galway really has everything. Its said that Galway is the gatekeeper of the Irish language and culture, where people can truly explore the real Ireland

name: Durhamstown Castle
description: You can find us on (SENSITIVE CONTENTS HIDDEN) and Instagram
neighborhood_overview: Our neighbourhood is very rural. The whole Celtic Tiger madness passed it by. Very lush rich farming land that changes very little. Ireland is famous for its grass & our Cattle &  horses are famous the world over.Every farmer dreams of breeding a "Shergar"! What is lovely about Meath is the richness of our ancient monuments-some pre-dating the Pyramids for God's sake.....a lot of them untouched & original which guests find really exciting. It's like you're discovering them. We also have an Art School nearby where you can study Life Drawing for a modest fee. There are two catch & release fishing places within 12 kms. An excellent riding stables & some beautiful golf courses. All within easy reach. A Coach can be arranged for day tripping.
host_about:
We like People-Family, our own youngsters, their partners, cousins, nieces/ nephews friends, colleagues, workmates et al...!
We cannot live without Beauty, Ethics, Music, fabulous/interesting Food, Films/ Books and Love, we strive for all of the above-sometimes we do fall short.......and,oh yes, Money, hard to live without that!
We love France and then we discovered Italy-Oh My God, sooooo beautiful. We visit London frequently as we have Family are there.
We really love our guests to feel "they're in their Granny's" when they stay here. (that would be a pretty cool Granny, mind you!) Its a drop- in-have-a-cup-of-coffee- kind of place anyway.
My Life motto is "everybody has needs and everybody's needs can be met".

name: Westport Writer's Cabin at Old Rectory
description: An Tigín- a small but perfectly formed wooden cabin in the grounds of Old Rectory Retreat.Your writing desk looks through glass doors to its' cottage garden by the stream. It has full kitchen facilities. Living and sleeping areas are semi-separated.
neighborhood_overview:
The surrounding area is a warren of lovely country walks on roads which don't have very much traffic (and on which cars cannot travel very fast anyway!) This makes it ideal for writers who need to refresh their batteries before sitting with laptop or paper again.
I can give you maps and guidelines.
Unfortunately, while we re only 5km fro Westport town, the Main road is no longer suitable for walking due to increased traffic. There is a longer cycling route (on laneway, country road and final stretch on coast road has a dedicated cycling path)

A little further afield and you reach Croagh Patrick, our holy mountain and a coastline on which there is a beach every few miles.

You can head for Leenane, the Killary and Connemara, our back garden.

Cycling is very popular especially the Greenway to Achill and bikes can be hired from Westport Town.

We are situated just 3 miles from Westport with all its’ tourist amenities, art and craft s
host_about:
I’m Róísín –  your hostess and general organiser. From the first time our family set eyes on The Old Rectory at Knappagh we knew we wanted to share it in some way with others…so this is a dream come true.  I’ve  written with and been involved in writers’ workshops on and off over the years and worked in amateur and community drama in one of many past lives. We feel our place offers a creative space in which people can work rest or just enjoy the surrounding area.
These days I have a new partner in my son Maitiú. Maitiú is 31 and has a business making cards from his art and words.  He helps keep the Tigín clean and tidy and welcomes guests.

name: Moytura Irish Mountain Retreat
description: Lovely Private 2 bedroom Retreat surrounded by Gorgeous views, History, and Serenity.
neighborhood_overview: The quiet nature loveliness of this place is amazing. If you sit quietly you might see a fox or a pheasant or rabbit come by. Walk up the back of the house and you will be surrounded by ancient fairy forts,battlefields, and fantastic views. Across the street is a 6 thousand year old, 20 foot high stone table. Walk right out the driveway and you will come to two loughs and an archery range. Go right out of the drive and you will crest the hill to see the majestic view of Lough Arrow. Continue down to see a Medieval Abbey and a historic estate...or just pop into the Bow and Arrow Pub for a pint....
host_about:
Dear Travelers,

I am an extremely social, nerdy, outdoors loving, book reading person. And I adore knowing at least a little bit about everything that is going on. 

I have a bunch of Irish influence which makes me a social story-teller who loves guests.  I enjoy hosting folks as well as traveling. I have spent time living in Argentina, Mexico, France, and Hawaii. I live in Ireland as well as in the States.

The house in Ireland is on my ancestor's land and I grew up going to this house. Previously my daughter and I spent a year remodeling and we hope you like the results.

A key thing about what I offer as a host is what I am looking for as a guest. I can't stand chain hotels. They can be quite luxurious but they always come across as impersonal. Give me a fun walkable neighborhood that real people live, work and play- and That is where I wish to stay. My properties are unique spaces that I created for myself, my family and my community that I can also share with you. 

One last thing, these are my personal properties so there are no surprises about folks who are subletting through Airbnb. I have a great team (Julie and others ) who take care of things when I am away, but you can always contact me directly through email, phone, or various apps with any concerns or questions.

I am a social person so hosting comes naturally to me and I have often had folks staying with me even before AirBnB and the other online booking agents.  Friends stay with me or just toss relations and friends my way to take in. Now thanks to the Share-economy so many things are possible that are community building, sustainable, and amazing.

Cheers,
Nola 
Owner of Moytura Retreat

name: Stunning Victorian apartment slps 6 - James Joyce
description:
Wonderful refurbished apartment that can sleep 6 comfortably.

Great features such as high ceilings, marble fireplace beautiful bay window.

Fully equipped kitchen, WiFi, cable TV parking if required are all included in the price.

Airport transfer can be arranged upon request for a fee.

Located just 3 min walk from supermarket, bakery, pharmacy etc.

Pubs and restuarants just 10 minute walk.

City centre 10 min by bus with excellent service right outside the front door.
neighborhood_overview:
This street is a beautifully tree lined street which runs right up the the entrance of the Phoenix Park.
This park is the largest urban park in Europe and houses Dublin Zoo and the presidential home and offices as well as a children's playground. It is a wonderful park to visit and spans over 1750 acres.
The street also has beautiful Victorian red bricked houses all along it which date back to the 18th century so it really is a taste of old Dublin.
There is a major supermarket just 2 minutes walk as well as a pharmacy, bakery, coffee shops, bars, restuarants and many other amenities all within easy walking distance.
host_about: I grew up in the tourist business as my parents ran a hotel in Kildare so I have always wanted to get back into the hosptality industry.  I have owned this house from the early '90's when I returned from New York where I had lived for a number of years.  I have been in the buidling trade for the last 20 years so I thought I would combine the two and refurbish the house and provide rental accommodation in an extremely convenient locations to tourists.

name: Very Special Oval Georgian Studio
description: Experience authentic Georgian elegance is this unique large OVAL studio apartment, overlooking park.  Accommodates two in cosy sleeping loft. Cook dinner in the designer kitchen, and then head out to enjoy the attractions of the city.
neighborhood_overview:
A beautiful, historic residential square, built in 1790's, within 5-10 minutes walk of down-town city centre. Elegance and convenience combined with a bit of inner city grittiness. I have loved it all, since 1978!

Mountjoy Square is situated just NE of the historic city centre, within walking distance of just about all the main city attractions. It is the most densely populated area in the entire city: 1500 people have front doors opening onto the Square.

The house fronts onto a 4acre/1.5ha park, across a fairly busy street. This apartment faces the side street, so it is quieter, but you will still hear traffic.....Please bear in mind that this is NOT LEAFY SUBURBIA, but a vibrant, living city community and it's definitely gritty in places... Having said that, I have lived here, uneventfully, for nearly 38 years, and consider the trade-offs well worth it, for the excitement and convenience of having the city on my doorstep..
host_about: Architectural enthusiast & committed urbanite, Alexander technique teacher, daily swimmer. I love to cook and to share meals with friends, and I aspire  to grow at least some of my own food. I love where I live, and enjoy all the amenities the city has to offer. I am Secretary of the Mountjoy Square Society, whose aim is to improve our area for all who live work and visit here. I am also a committee member of the Irish Georgian Society, and I regularly organize  day trips and walking tours for our members.

name: Beautiful Coastal Cottage West Cork
description:
A unique 3 bedroom seaside cottage nestled in the outstandingly beautiful surroundings of the Seven Heads, West Cork. Recharge at this peaceful, stress free retreat for up to 7 people. The open plan sitting room and kitchen downstairs is floored with rustic slate and beautiful rugs, with large windows providing a stunning vista of rolling Irish countryside.
After a day spent on our breathtaking beaches, you can unwind with a sundowner on your balcony or a bbq in the garden.
neighborhood_overview:
This thrillingly remote retreat offers all the bonuses of an ‘off-grid hideaway’ but is within easy reach of a range of West Cork’s vibrant, bustling towns and villages, from musical Clonakilty to historic Kinsale and beyond…
Dunworley Bay sits on a rugged and enchanting stretch of Atlantic coast known as the Seven Heads. So if you love long, beautiful walks along headlands, exploring ring forts and watch towers or climbing along rocky coastline discovering untouched coves and beaches- this is heaven!
The areas offers a range of activities from cycling, to riding and all kinds of water sports. We love surfing, kayaking, rock jumping, swimming and body-boarding at Dunworley Beach- all year round if you’re brave!

Fishermen will delight that there is excellent fishing straight from the beach, or Richard can take you out in the bay in our little boat to catch some mackerel.

The sands are washed clean by the lovely unpolluted sea every day, the air is fresh
host_about:
My husband Richard and I live in the spectacularly beautiful area of West Cork, Dunworley, where we host guests in our three properties. The properties are a 4 minute walk from Dunworley Beach and we relish sharing this incredibly special part of Ireland with people from all over the world. 
We have a small garden in West Cork which we farm organically and use our produce to cater for guests if they so wish. 
Get in touch and see how we can help with your special Irish trip of a lifetime.

name: Best location balcony St Patrick's view
description: Bright, cosy one bedroom apartment in the heart of the south city centre.  The location could not be bettered for visiting Dublin's museums, pubs, restaurants, theatres and cafes.  Fully equipped kitchen, balcony,, reliable wifi.  From the balcony you have a view of St Patrick's Cathedral and the adjacent park.  There is no elevator so it is unfortunately not suitable for people with mobility issues.  St. Stephen's Green/ Grafton St. and Dame St/ Temple Bar are a 10 minute stroll.
neighborhood_overview: It is in the heart of the city centre.  You can walk anywhere you want to be in a matter of minutes.  I love the location, and the atmosphere in the heart of old Dublin.  There are lots of great pubs, restaurants and cafes, Francis St (the antiques district), St Patrick's Cathedral and park (love to hear the bells).  It is very safe.
host_about:
Hello.  I am a professional living in Dublin city centre with my husband.   I have lived abroad and love to travel.  My interests include food, cinema, reading and spending time with friends.  We love having people over for dinner and meeting new people.    We also love eating out.

Of the places I have visited for pleasure, I especially loved India, Bali, Brazil, Bolivia, Laos and Japan.  I really enjoy meeting people when I travel she getting local recommendations.  I love all of the Mediterranean and Hong Kong.  I love reading anything set in India or anything by Douglas Kennedy, Anne Tyler.  My monthly book club is something I really look forward to.

We have really enjoyed meeting new people through Airbnb.  We are pretty passionate about Dublin, and like to share all the places that we think are special with visitors.   Edgar says that Dubliners can be the most friendly people in the world!

We now have 2 cats living with us.   The cats will be on holiday when you rent our home.

name: Long Loft Room at The Bastion
description: Our most spacious and unique room at The  Bastion. There is a double bed and a single bed. Max capacity is 2 people in this room. Breakfast is not included but it's available right next door at The Bastion Kitchen. Free WiFi. Ensuite bathroom.
host_about:
Hi there! We’re brothers Anthony & Vinny McCay and  we run The Bastion. Our street is named after the Royal Bastion which once occupied the street where we are.

 Our house is a bit of a labyrinth inside. There's lots of history here. The world famous Irish tenor John Count McCormack often visited in the early 1900s.  Our great great grandfather Michael Kilkelly was his first tutor.

Our style is laid back and relaxed. We love good food and the left bank area  is a gourmet district with lots of great restaurants and pubs. You definitely won't go hungry here.  Ireland's Oldest Bar is just down the hill. There is music most evenings. 

The beautiful river Shannon is just at the end of the street. The imposing and enormous stone castle built by King John in 1210 majestically guards the river crossing. 

In 1691 the area was besieged by the armies of King William of Orange in a battle with King James for the English throne.  Twelve thousand cannon balls were fired across the river in the barrage that ensued. We have one of them!

The nearby  Luan Gallery hosts great exhibitions throughout the year.

name: Peaceful Cottage in Mayo farmland
description: Many visitors to Ireland tour the BnB/pub circuit. Stay at Peaceful Cottage and tour locally. The local ancient place name is Mochara (mu-harra) meaning stony place. The fields and farms are girded with stone walls & Mochara Castle overlooks all.
neighborhood_overview:
Peaceful Cottage is an Irish self-catering cottage in County Mayo in the West of Ireland. Centrally located for day trips to all the best attractions Ireland has to offer.

•Galway City located at the mouth of Galway Bay is both a picturesque and lively city with a wonderful avant-garde culture and a fascinating mixture of locally owned, specialty shops, often featuring locally made crafts. Galway sits beside the village of Claddagh, the birth place of the Claddagh ring and the famous Claddagh Story.

•Ashford Castle in Cong is a 10 minute car ride from the Peaceful Cottage. Take a wonderful ferry ride on Lough Corrib. John Wayne's home-coming movie "The Quiet Man" was filmed in Cong, Maam and on the Connemara.

•Golf Ballinrobe's 18 hole Championship Parkland Course. Claremorris has a 9 hole course. Oughterard has an 18 hole course and Westport has an 18 hole Championship course. Cloonacastle, Ballinrobe, Co. Mayo, Ireland. Tel: +353 (0)94 954-1118
host_about: I am a product developer in engineering however my real passions are skiing in the Rockies and bicycling in Ireland.

name: Elegant & Romantic - Relaxing Stay
description: Georgian townhouse, central Birr. A spacious, elegant room with touches of luxury, add to the experience of sleeping in an antique four-poster bed. Non-suite guest bathroom. Wallow in the original bath by candlelight (Prosecco extra!) This B&B has been greatly enjoyed over many years by writers, musicians, visitors & tourists from around the World. Listed in renowned guidebooks, it's a home with art, antiques & many books.  Indulgent *breakfast. (*Or Light Breakfast option.) Free street parking.
neighborhood_overview:
I love a great deal about our 'neighbourhood'...where to start?
Though I may add more later, might I begin by extolling the virtues of this small, midlands heritage town, with its layers of fascinating history. Not just for its friendly, diversely interesting and some a touch eccentric, people; but also for the attractive architecture, the cultural joys of our theatre, the lovely parks and the proximity to such beautiful walks by the river, and in the mountains close by.

Some of the following information is currently being updated. We have a printed guide available to visitors, listing our favoured dining and drinking places.

Excellent local public swimming pool, sauna etc, and gym facility. (Solar powered). Also a pool and gym at the County Arms Hotel. Skate park; Children's playground; Tennis, golf course; hurling and rugby pitches; outdoor pursuits, hillwalking, canal strolls and bikeways. Horse trekking in the mountains...and more.

Are you a
host_about:
An 'occasional' writer, artist/designer. Family background was in historic property restoration - homes open to the public. Later lived & worked in London & New York for architects as a colour & materials specialist.
Very happily settled back in Ireland in this busy, arty heritage town, running Tin Jug Studio (first art gallery in the county) - now occasionally open for seasonal children's art classes, events, screenings, exhibitions, etc.

name: Galway Bay Sea View Apartments 2 bedroom
description: Welcome to the Galway Bay Sea View apartments in Salthill. These apartments have a bright, airy interior and fully-equipped kitchen. With a designated dining area, comfy beds and a terrace with views of Galway Bay, you’ll have an unforgettable stay. Enjoy activities at the beach, nearby attractions and a glass of Guinness while watching the sunset. Check-in securely and stress-free with self-check in kiosk. Whether for a weekend getaway or a relaxing retreat, you won’t be disappointed here.
neighborhood_overview:
Galway City as well as the Galway County offers its visitors a lot of attractions. The historic ‘City of the Tribes’ itself is a lovely and vibrant place with bustling streets and outgoing people. After a full day of sightseeing, hiking or playing golf you can rest in a cosy and friendly atmosphere of the city’s pubs and restaurants. During the summer months, Galway becomes the home of exceptional entertainment events like the Galway Races or the Galway Arts Festival. Its location makes it a perfect base for tours to Connemara , the magnificent Cliffs of Moher and other sights in counties of Mayo and Clare.
All three counties surrounding Galway are soaked in history and studded with amazing castles and mansions, which differ not only in size and shape but also setting and atmosphere. Some of them are surrounded by beautiful gardens suitable for walks and rest, whilst others are perched on hillsides. Among the most beautiful are The Abbeyglen Castle, The Lynch’s Castle, and Ashford
host_about:
GALWAY BAY SEA VIEW APARTMENTS
Located in the desirable seaside resort of Salthill; the mid-way point on the Wild Atlantic Way, within easy reach of the bustling medieval city of Galway to the East and the Gateway to Connemara to the West.

Galway Bay Sea View Apartments offer you the ideal base from which to discover the local environs or venturing further afield to explore the surrounding historical sites and expansive National Parks in Connemara and County Clare.

Each spacious apartment has its own private balcony or a roof top terrace presenting a stunning, panoramic vista of Galway Bay along with views of the Clare Hills and dramatic Burren landscape. Stylishly furnished with all the amenities you expect in your home from home accommodation and where your comfortable and relaxing stay awaits. The unrivalled views of Galway Bay, coupled with a seaside village vibe, ensure a refreshing experience every time.

These spacious, contemporary apartments offer freedom and flexibility for both the leisure and corporate visitor alike with space to relax or work in.

Suitable for families, friends and colleagues alike each apartment has a fully equipped kitchen with washing machine, dishwasher and a microwave leading on to an open plan dining/lounge area. The open plan area features an expandable dining table for up to 6 people, a 32-inch flat-screen TV and digital TV box with over 100 channels and individual, fast, reliable free Wi-Fi.

Complimentary on-site parking and complimentary fast, reliable Wi-Fi included in all prices.

name: "The Cobbler" Rosscarbery Holiday Cottage
description: Welcome to The Cobbler a Cozy 3-Bedroom charming home in Rosscarbery. Walk to Shops & Pubs, perfect for up to 6 guests. Just a short walk from the town square, this cozy retreat offers a spacious living area, a fully equipped kitchen, and three comfortable bedrooms. Relax in the enclosed garden or explore nearby pubs, restaurants, golf, pitch & put, Lagoon Activity Centre, Smugglers Cove and scenic coastal walks. A perfect home away from home for a peaceful or adventure-filled getaway!
neighborhood_overview:
The Cobbler holiday house is a four star holiday home.
It is a three bedroomed house which can comfortably accommodate up to six people, and is situated in the popular picturesque coastal town of Rosscarbery.

It is located within easy walking distance to the shops, pubs, Celtic Ross Hotel and a number of restaurants in the village.

The house is situated less than 2km from the Warren Beach and pitch& putt club. Less than 1km is the Rosscarbery golf range.
Rosscarbery is a small historic town set in picturesque surroundings overlooking a sandy inlet of the rugged West Cork coastline.

A coastal inlet forms a logoon next to the town where it is possible to rent out paddle boats and canoes. For children there is a playground nearby and a tennis court.

For those who just want to relax, the Warren Beach, Ownahincha Beach and the Long Strand offer safe bathing and golden sands.

name: City Centre Apartment | Temple Bar | Dublin Castle
description: Fantastic, top-floor, two-bedroom apartment in a beautiful, old building in the very, very heart of Dublin City. Dublin City is quite literally at your fingertips! This is the best located Airbnb listing in Dublin - and that's no exaggeration.
neighborhood_overview:
Have a glance at a map of Dublin and you'll see that Dame Street is right in the centre of everything that Dublin has to offer. Trinity College is at one end of Dame Street (3 minute walk from the apartment) and Christ Church Cathedral is at the other (2 minute walk in the other direction). On one side is Dublin Castle and City Hall, and on the other is Temple Bar.

All other notable parts of the city – such as Grafton Street area, St Stephens Green, Merrion Square, O'Connell Street – are within a 10-15 minute walk.

As well as being immersed in Dublin's history and culture, you're surrounded by the best cafes, restaurants, pubs and shopping in Dublin.
host_about: A native Dubliner back living in Dublin after stints in New York, London and the West of Ireland. Fond of travelling but always happy to get back to Dublin. The apartment I have listed is right in the very centre of Dublin City - very genuinely, it couldn't be any more central; the centre of the centre, if you like.

name: Ninorc house in beautiful Bantry
description: Ninorc is a 19th century Irish farmhouse that has been faithfully restored and modernised to bring it up to 21st century standards. The house is on a working farm and your host Breda lives on this farm with her family.
neighborhood_overview: Bantry is a friendly and tolerant market town situated on Bantry Bay, which is one of Ireland's largest and deepest harbours. Nearby are other harbour towns such as Kenmare, Schull and Baltimore. Please note guests booking for the months of June, July and August must book from Saturday to Saturday.
host_about:
My husband and I have been running Ninorc Farmhouse for the last ten years. I am a retired hospital manager and nurse and my husband Michael is the farmer. As a retiree, I keep busy by growing my own vegetables in a garden and in a green house, minding my grand-children and lots of walking. Two of my adult sons and their wives and children also live on the farm and we have two dogs - Coco a bichon frieze and a cattle dog called Max. 

The farm is a dry stock farm - this means the cattle are raised for beef. We also keep pigs and have laying hens so plenty of eggs! Most evenings, I walk along the sea front in Bantry, which is great for getting rid of any stress. I am also a volunteer collector with the Cork Cancer Research Centre, a medical research organisation founded by my brother. 

As for my own travels, since retirement we have been on a road trip of California and Western Canada. We finished our Canada trip by visiting my husband's niece in Toronto who runs a lively Irish bar - McCarthy's Bar. In California, we loved the wine country, especially the small towns dotted amidst the rolling vineyards. 

And why NINORC farmhouse? Well, we thought long and hard about a distinctive name for the house and came up with the family name spelled backwards. Simple really!

name: Woodland Hideaway on the Kerry Coast
description: Spacious & stylish contemporary cottage, nestled in a secluded wooded area under the Seefin mountain. The property has a wonderful rustic retreat feel to it, sure to relax and recharge in equal measure. It is surrounded by the Caragh river, lake and sea, and situated a mile from Glenbeigh village on the majestic Ring of Kerry.
host_about:
Originally from the best of the west coast, and currently working in Dublin. Things I love include music (being a musician myself), the outdoors, hitting the water, the changing of the seasons, architecture/design, good books, great films, funky art, fine coffee, stimulating conversation, meeting new people....and of course travelling to interesting new places. I have traveled far and wide throughout this world of ours, and now take great pleasure in welcoming people to my own little patch of it.

I finished building my Kerry cottage home in 2012. It was a genuine labour of love; fulfilling a long held ambition to have my own beautiful place in the beautiful area I grew up in. name: En suite prívate cottage stay at an Organic Farm
description:
Welcome to An Tionól Cottage
A place of rest, simplicity, and connection.
Nestled in the heart of nature, this old Irish stone cottage has been lovingly restored over the past two decades. Surrounded by gardens and wild beauty, it’s a space to slow down, breathe deeply, and feel at home.
We are a family who values the richness of a life rooted in the land, and we’re happy to share this special place with you.
neighborhood_overview:
An Tionól cottage and its surroundings are magical. You can find native woodland, lakes, and tiny roads that give you the opportunity to go for walks in a very charming Irish countryside landscape.
The surrounding and gentle vibe of An Tionól allows you to unwind and reset from having been met by the simplicity of nature of this special and ancestral part of Ireland.

Describ

Sarah :)

name: Historic Nile Lodge House , Galway City, sleeps 10
description:
Nile Lodge is a prestigious, private residence in the heart of the cultural city of Galway. The property is perfectly located just 5 minutes walk from both the Salthill promenade and all the major attractions of the city. Far enough for the tranquility and quiet, whilst also having the convenience of the finest restaurants and coffee shops, live music and delightful Irish pubs.
It is an ideal venue for a private holiday with easy access to some of the most beautiful scenery of Ireland.
neighborhood_overview:
The area is very friendly and one of the most describable parts of Galway city. There is a early opening and late closing small grocery shop in the Maxol Garage directly across the road and 2 supermarkets within a 4 minute walk. Morton's delicatessen with fresh bread and cakes daily is a 4 minute walk away.

We are a 5 to 7 minute walk from the Latin Quarter in the city center, and a 4 minute walk to the Salthill seaside promenade, with wonderful scenic views of Galway Bay. The promenade is a perfect place for seaside strolls or jogging.

Plenty of gyms, spas and swimming pools around the area. You can hire bikes from a few rental places in town.

The Wild Atlantic Way route goes right through Galway and passes within 500 yards of the house.
host_about:
I have been hosting Nile Lodge for many years now and have had the great privilege of meeting some truly wonderful people during that time.
 I had a fabulous time in 2021 as a film extra on the upcoming movie, the Banshees of  Inisherin.
I am wearing the clothing for this in my profile picture, just in case any future guest thinks I look like this all the time!
My hobbies are fairly simple, I enjoy theater, especially the Druid productions, film, music, reading , chatting, walking, messing around in the garden.

name: Traditional Farm 'The Small Cottage'
description: This Small Cottage which Sleeps 2 is just lovely and compact, with its open fire and leisurely ambience, it makes the perfect retreat. It is quiet and peaceful. You can enjoy a relaxing walk around the farm,  just read or write a book or plan day trips to  many local attractions or scenic sites !
neighborhood_overview:
Fairy Fort Farm is situated about 2 km from the Village of Borrisoleigh, with its traditional Irish village layout ! It has a beautiful Parish church, a Sportsfield , and Community Centre to be proud of , Pubs, cafe, petrol filling stations, shops, Grocery, Post Office, DIY , Doctors, Garda Station and takeaway restaurants.

We like to preserve nature and do our bit to help biodiversity. We don't use any chemicals or sprays on the land and allow patches of ground to grow as they like, making it a haven for wildlife. If the beautiful sound of birdsong annoys you, maybe you should look elsewhere. Likewise, if you are seeking acres of manicured gardens, then this is not the place for you. If you want to enjoy nature at its finest, with glorious hedgerows harbouring multitudes of life and natural meadows with mixed grasses and wildflowers providing sustenance to pollinators, then you are most welcome to share this special place for your visit. Guests sometimes come, planning to
host_about:
I am easygoing. I like fun, good conversation, music, art, picnics, walking, cycling. I take an occasional drink in company. I like travelling, new experiences. etc. I'm into sustainability, promoting biodiversity and taking climate action. I'm trying to grow some of my own food and try to reduce waste through repair, reuse and recycling. 
Life is good :)

I hope Fairy Fort Farm will become a mecca of love , nurturing and creativity !

name: Cosy Traditional Ivy Farm Cottage
description: The lovely thing here is the quiet and relaxing peace of this little cottage. With the open fire and also the South facing frontage this is indeed a most welcoming place to just take some time out and recharge your batteries. Enjoy dining outside or just having a cup of tea on the picnic table outside the front door. The cottage is over 100 years old with traditional features. Upstairs rooms are best suited for children due to sloping ceilings.
neighborhood_overview:
Tranquility and peace are my friends here at FFF. the stream, waterfall, and new woodland is all such a pleasure and dare I say it, spiritual !
You have Free access to the farm and all the lovely walks, both on the farm and on the local mountains. There is also a great traditional music culture in this area.
Your cottage is close to the owners, so you have instant access should you have any enquiries , or if you are looking for hot tips on places to visit , stories and legends from the area, etc.

We like to preserve nature and do our bit to help biodiversity. We don't use any chemicals or sprays on the land and allow patches of ground to grow as they like, making it a haven for wildlife. If the beautiful sound of birdsong annoys you, maybe you should look elsewhere. Likewise, if you are seeking acres of manicured gardens, then this is not the place for you. If you want to enjoy nature at its finest, with glorious hedgerows harbouring multitudes of life and natural
host_about:
I am easygoing. I like fun, good conversation, music, art, picnics, walking, cycling. I take an occasional drink in company. I like travelling, new experiences. etc. I'm into sustainability, promoting biodiversity and taking climate action. I'm trying to grow some of my own food and try to reduce waste through repair, reuse and recycling. 
Life is good :)

FISHING ON THE RIVER ILEN

Also very popular in Skibbereen is Salmon & Sea Trout Fishing on the Ilen River.
The River Ilen is a medium sized spate river about 21 miles (33kms.) long and flows through some of the most beautiful scenery in West Cork. A large part of the river is managed by the River Ilen Anglers' Club based in Skibbereen. The season for Salmon & Sea Trout opens on February 15th and closes on September 30th for Salmon and on October 12th for Sea Trout.

SALMON

name: Cute Cottage Carrigaholt West Clare
description: This traditional stone fronted cottage is nestled on the picturesque Loop Head Peninsula in the tranquil fishing village of Carrigaholt in County Clare, West Ireland. Carrigaholt is located along the route of the "Wild Atlantic Way". The dramatic coastline is awash with towering cliffs and unique rock formations, flourishing wildlife and sea-life. The area is famous for dolphin watching, fishing, walking treks, cycling routes, seafood, and of course the pint of Guinness!
neighborhood_overview:
In The Area:
﻿-The Loop Head peninsula has some of the most spectacular cliff scenery in Europe, look up websites: loophead eden, dolphinwatch carrigaholt, loopheadclare, loophead, wildatlanticway, and thelongwayround for guided walks
-Sea and shore angling locations
-Carrigaholt sea angling centre
-E-bike hire in Carrigaholt
-Horse riding at Carmen's riding school Querrin
-Dolphin watching boat trips which operates from Carrigaholt and Kilrush
-Many top class golf courses in the surrounding areas of Kilkee, Kilrush, Doonbeg and Lahinch
-Lahinch surfing beach and The Cliffs of Moher are located about 45 minutes away. The Burren is only an hour's drive away.
-Carrigaholt also has a long beach suitable for swimming.
-Four lively pubs including the multi-award winning Long Dock Bar and Restaurant, 'The Barnyard' an open air coffee shop, and a Take away.
host_about: I am an artist living in Clare with my husband. Let us share with you our little slice of heaven.

name: Rosslare Strand Rooms Only accommodation
description:
Our modern Rooms Only accommodation is in the seaside village, a 2 minute walk from a 4km white sand beach. We have 3 bedrooms, 1 with double bed and 2 with twin beds (2 single beds) Each room has its own ensuite, shower & toilet. A delicious breakfast is now available in the new adjacent hotel for an extra fee, there are 5 options to choose from including a vegetarian option, full Irish, 3 egg omelettes and light continental fare, all reasonably priced.
The village has 2 deluxe hotels now, one with a luxurious spa. There are many places to dine out, including the 2 hotels, an award winning seafood restaurant, a gastro pub, a Chinese restaurant, a pizza place, 2 cafes
and 2 fish and chip restaurants. There are 2 golf courses as well as lovely walks on the beach. Historic Wexford town is a 20 minute drive and beautiful Johnstown castle is a 15 minute drive away.
We look forward to meeting you at our lovely location.
Esoteric Healing Sessions now available at t
neighborhood_overview:
There is a strong local community spirit here and lots of tourists come for the blue flag beach which has very safe swimming for children. There are also 2 golf courses and a driving range within walking distance. There is the very popular outdoor bowling green at the local Community Center and tennis courts for hire, lessons are available also. There is a lovely playground for children and a beautiful community garden to explore.... The local historic town of Wexford is a 20 minute drive away. Beautiful Johnstown castle is a short 15 minute drive away, with tea rooms and amazing gardens and walks.
Since we are rooms only there are no kitchen facilities here. However there are many places to eat in the village and you are welcome to bring back take-out food to eat in the tea room here. It is a real break for the "Cook" of the house, usually hard-working Moms, enjoy the many culinary delights Rosslare has to offer!
host_about: I am a student of life who likes to meet people from all over the world and learn what works for them as well as sharing what works for me in all areas of life, from the fun and interesting to the global chaos we seem to be steeped in these days. I like to walk the lovely beach location we live in and do oil painting  when time permits. Good food is also a must, fresh from the farmers market and fish shop we have some of the best produce in Ireland, Wexford is famous for strawberries and potatoes and local fresh fish! We do our best to accommodate all our guest requests and we look forward to meeting you.

name: Perfect Location City Centre House
description: Two bedroom period red brick terraced house on a quiet, tree-lined street in the heart of the city centre. Just off Patrick St.  There are two double bedrooms, one shower room, kitchen and living/dining room.  The house was fully refurbished and insulated.  It is very cosy and warm Roof terrace.  The interior is all white with some original features, including a working fireplace in the living room. WiFi, SMART TV, Apple TV.  Under floor heating downstairs..  This is our home.
neighborhood_overview:
It is right in the heart of the city centre and yet on a very quiet tree lined street. I like the traditional redbrick fronts of the houses and the fact that you can be in Temple Bar, Grafton Street or St Stephens Green in less than ten minutes. St Patrick's Cathedral and Christchurch and Christchurch Cathedral are minutes away. There is a great selection of traditional pubs and fashionable cafes.

Everything Dublin city centre has to offer is within walking distance.
host_about:
Hello.  I am a professional living in Dublin city centre with my husband.   I have lived abroad and love to travel.  My interests include food, cinema, reading and spending time with friends.  We love having people over for dinner and meeting new people.    We also love eating out.

Of the places I have visited for pleasure, I especially loved India, Bali, Brazil, Bolivia, Laos and Japan.  I really enjoy meeting people when I travel she getting local recommendations.  I love all of the Mediterranean and Hong Kong.  I love reading anything set in India or anything by Douglas Kennedy, Anne Tyler.  My monthly book club is something I really look forward to.

We have really enjoyed meeting new people through Airbnb.  We are pretty passionate about Dublin, and like to share all the places that we think are special with visitors.   Edgar says that Dubliners can be the most friendly people in the world!

We now have 2 cats living with us.   The cats will be on holiday when you rent our home.

name: Luxury Room,Grand Canal,City Center
description:
I am delighted to offer you a double room in my stylish 2-bed apartment located on the 4th floor in Grand Canal Dock area. Guests enjoy this bedroom and a private bathroom and share the kitchen and living space with my partner, Caitriona, and me.

My apartment is in a lively, welcoming and safe area just 15-20 minutes walk from Dublin's bustling city centre. My place is your home away from home!

Please feel free to contact me if you have any questions about my place or Dublin...Thank you!
neighborhood_overview:
The Grand Canal Dock area, which is on our doorstep is packed with great restaurants, cute cafes and lively local bars.

There are five great event spaces near my apartment:
1. Bord Gais Energy Theatre - showcases some of the best musicals, opera and ballet in Dublin - is right next to the apartment.
2. The Dublin Convention Centre, which hosts many international conferences & events is directly across the River Liffey from my place (3 minute walk)
3. The 3Arena, a ten minute walk, is a large concert venus will host international acts including Bruno Mars, Aerosmith and Radiohead in 2017
4. Aviva Stadium, home to Irish Rugby & Soccer, is a 20 minute walk along the Grand Canal.
5. Croke Park, the home of our national sports games and also many concerts throughout the summer like Bruce Springstein, Beyonce & Take That, is a 25 minute walk from our place.
host_about:
I am a freelance chef.  I have worked around the world on board yachts, in villas and private homes.

My favourite city is New York. I love visiting Thailand for the amazing food. I enjoy travelling all over the world but always love coming home to Dublin. I am pretty passionate about Dublin, and like to share all the places that I think are special with visitors. I work in the restaurant industry so I have many of recommendations for great places to eat in the area.

I am a really sociable and active person with a love for the sea and travelling. I enjoy diving, skiing, swimming, wake-board/water-skiing and hiking.  My main passion in life is food.

I have been a host on Airbnb since March 2013 and so far it's been an amazing experience. I have really enjoyed meeting so many new people.

Exceptional view from 3 windows of living area of 'The Sleeping Giant' & Killery Mountains. Quiet & secluded, peaceful retreat, on a mature site, Situated 8 miles from Sligo town. High speed Fibre Broadband now available at the property & privacy fence installed Autumn 2021.
neighborhood_overview: We are located 2 miles from The Lake Isle of Innisfree, 8 miles from Sligo town, 3 miles to a wonderful walk at Slishwood or Dooney Rock. The cottage is ideally located for those attending weddings in Markree Castle (10 mins) or Castledargan Hotel (6 min drive). Morans bar in Ballintogher is doing good food on Friday & Saturday nights. Also does Sunday lunch.  Great food also available 3 miles away in the village of Dromahair, in the Riverbank.

name: Leap B&B.
description: Close to the village but quiet and secluded. The house is a home and full of interest . I love my garden and the hillside around and that at night it is dark and quiet [rather than traffic noise I hear a fox bark or an owl hoot up the hill] We have two cats.
neighborhood_overview: I think of Leap as the beginning of wild West Cork. Here the coastline begins to become rugged with endless coves to explore. It is a great base from which to explore . The village is quiet but has several pubs and places in which to eat out.
host_about:
I like one to one conversation, gardening, travelling and good food [healthy usually but not always] I love reading, drawing/painting, walking , intelligent conversation...

People and life interest me . I am a member of Couchsurfing and people who have stayed said that I am very welcoming and kind.

I am quite quiet ...not the life and soul of the party. However, I am warm , thoughtful and welcoming and will care about your comfort ...your stay. I love West Cork and know quite a lot about its history and can direct you to various places of historical interest locally. What I won't want to do is take you to local pubs etc. I will point you in a particular direction and leave it to you.

name: Cosy, self-contained, 1-bed space.
description: Clean, private and spacious self-contained space, suit couple. About 20 mins walk to O'Connell Street. Fully fitted bathroom, kitchen/living room, separate double bedroom. Near shops, pubs, and public transport.  Suit quiet, non-smoking couple. Very good public transport, including the newly extended tram. You can get a tram just a few minutes walk away from the flat and it's only 4 stops into O'Connell Street!
neighborhood_overview:
Phibsborough (also spelled Phibsboro) is very convenient in that it is near to all amenities, e.g. shops, cafes and public transport. It is also within easy access to the centre of the City, so guests can choose to avail of the tranquility of their apartment or the busy nightlife of the city.
Convenient to Croke Park, The Botanic Gardens, The Phoenix Park and Glasnevin Museum. Also within easy reach of the Gate Theatre, Dublin Writers' Museum and other attractions.
It's even easier to get to the city centre now, using the newly opened Luas tram line. Only 4 stops to O'Connell Street!

name: Tranquil Cottage in the Heart of Kerry
description: Robins Rest cottage is situated in the heart of Caragh Lake on the famous Ring of Kerry, Wild Atlantic Way & Reeks District. Nearby Killorglin  town is famous for the Puck Fair Festival and Killarney is just 20 mins drive away. Rossbeigh beach has 5 km of beach and a 20 minute stroll will bring you to Caragh Lake, truly spectacular. The cottage is a tranquil space, newly refurbished, with plenty space  inside and out to  sit and relax. The cottage is in a perfect location for exploring.
neighborhood_overview: Kerry is famous for its beauty and there is an abundance of places to visit by car or walks close by. There is something for everyone from golf to horse riding, hiking, fishing and yoga and meditation. The cottage is on a quiet country road scattered with cottages and bungalows. In the fields are donkeys, horses and mainly cattle. I always have a few carrots to hand for the donkeys and horses.
host_about: I love to travel and see the world. I am an animal lover and rescue many dogs. As a host, I hope to offer you a wonderful stay at Robins Rest Cottage. I have just started this July 23. I love my little cottage and enjoy spending time there. It’s is a beautiful space, offering peace and tranquility. I hope you enjoy it too.

name: Relaxing and cosy Pink Room!
description: Old stone cottage built in the 1700's rennovated slowly over the last 20 years - and still ongoing!  Private access to river, bathroom only used by the 2 guest rooms and catering facilities shared with owner, however you MUST check first to see if the kitchen is available when you are here as I cater for WWOOF volunteers who help here as well.  Dogs, cats, views, sea within 20 mins walk. Lively household with artists and environmentalists. Child friendly.
neighborhood_overview: West Cork is one of the most beautiful areas of Ireland and I keep maps and brochures of local sites and activities for guests to use.
host_about: I'm English, but have been living in West Cork for over 20 years, having Irish ancestry and feel I have come home.  Originally a teacher I moved on to work as an Arts Manager, specialising in large outdoor events and community Arts through which I was an Environmental Educator for 14 years with my own company.  I like to garden and I like to build!  I have been developing my place to be a residential Arts Centre since I arrived here, with the help of friends and volunteers, especially through the WWOOF programme, which I now manage for the island of Ireland.

description:
Dromforde is a B and B and offers you beauty and style. This is our 13th year as a SuperHost.

Dromforde gives you the privacy of 2 very comfortable bedrooms, private shower room and WC, sitting room/dining room with wood burning stove, with your own private entrance. There are beautiful gardens.

Bantry Cinemax Cinema

host_about:
I love this area and I love living with the history of a West Cork farmhouse. We enjoy walking with our dog and nothing 'detoxes' the mental system and feeds the spirit better than a walk on a wild, stormy beach. 
Living in the  countryside has put us in touch with the passing of the seasons and the beautiful, ever changing, range of colours on the hills in front of Dromforde tell me the time of the year.Brigid and I Established our garden and we shared the pleasure of eating all the fruit and veg that we grow. I Ihope that you will enjoy our garden while you stay with me.

I  am  the typical 'Shed man', mending making or just tinkering in his workshop.
 
I wish to welcome you to Dromforde will try and give you the very best time while  being my guest in Dromforde.

name: Stylish Nohoval Town House
description: Surrounded by perfect nature, rain or shine, this home is located in the peaceful little village of Nohoval, famous for it's Cove.  This countryside between Cork and Kinsale is off the beaten track. However no public transport, so a car or bike needed. Ideal for nature lovers, walking, cycling, cliffs, beaches, cold water swimming or sauna and a dip...all nearby. The house is loved by owner Aine who will give you great tips on the local experience. It's  a place to catch a breath and slow down.
host_about: I'm finally back in Nohoval and ready to share my home and the perfect nature of South Cork with guests. For the last decade most of my life has been in South India, on the east coast where I could surf and be by the sea. Besides surfing, I love to travel and meet people, mostly by the ocean. For now I'm at home and looking forward to the travellers visiting me. I think of the quote "there are no strangers here, only friends you haven't met yet".

Come and stay in Dublin’s shortest street - in vibrant Stonybatter.
The place is compact,warm, quiet, safe and secure.

A kitchen diner, two double bedrooms plus two bathrooms and a small covered yard.

name: Thatched Cottage by the Sea
description: A 300 year old thatched cottage across the road from Annestown Beach. Annestown is a beautiful little village in the sunny south east of Ireland. It is a quaint and quiet spot surrounded by stunning scenery. The remarkable thing about Annestown is that it hasn't been touched by new development, leaving it close to how it would have been hundreds of years ago. Annestown is along the Copper Coast. The area was declared a European Geopark in 2001 and a UNESCO Global Geopark in 2004.
neighborhood_overview: Quaint little seaside village. No shops or pubs in the village. There is a Church of Ireland church and Annestown beach is the highlight. Access to the Anne Valley walkway at the bottom of the village.
host_about: I am a nature enthusiast, visual artist and mother. Love meeting people from different places and swapping stories. Have trotted around the globe for a bit and have a great love for West Africa. I split my time between Ireland and New York.

name: Kinsale - Cosy home from home
description:
Cosy house in centre of Kinsale on historic Stoney Steps.
Home from Home.
Start your Wild Atlantic Way journey here!
neighborhood_overview:
Wonderfully quirky town with great pubs and restaurants. Gateway to West Cork & Wild Atlantic Way with amazing scenery, towns & craftspeople. Happy planning!

The town centre is an easy 1 minute walk. Old Head Golf Course is 10 minutes' drive. Kinsale has a natural enclosed harbour at the mouth of the Bandon River. It is protected by two ancient fortresses, Charles Fort and James Fort, built in the early 17th century. The town is well-known for its medieval Georgian and Victorian architecture and its maze of narrow streets. Yachting, fine restaurants, authentic pubs and terrific shopping are at your doorstep. Shannon Airport is 63 miles. Cork is 15 miles. Killarney is 50 miles. Kinsale is a historic town and is famous for its gourmet restaurants, breathtaking views and old town centre.

This area of South West Ireland is of outstanding beauty with its dramatic coastline, unspoilt locations and safe beaches. Leisure activities are well catered for, Kinsale provides
host_about:
Marketer and traveller. I live in Dublin but rent out Kinsale - my home from home. When I am not working, I like to try new things and see new places. Love reading and lots of sport including hurling, rugby and golf. 

Come visit!

name: The Greenway Dungarvan
description:
Four bed home at West Waterford Golf Club, 3 miles/10 minutes drive from Dungarvan town.

Consists of 4 bedrooms and 3 bathrooms. Sleeps 6. Private patio area with BBQ, outdoor dining area & tennis court.

The house has been lovingly designed for family friendly holidays & creative, cosy retreats alike. Close to beaches, woodland, mountains, the Greenway Cycle Route, Dungarvan town, Waterford and Cork city, our art-filled holiday home is the perfect base for a fun and relaxing getaway.
neighborhood_overview:
West Waterford is a hidden gem, with the newly opened Greenway Cycle Path, extensive coastline, mountains and a wonderful river valleys on the doorstep. Dungarvan is the perfect base from which to explore with many fine beaches for swimming, and secluded lanes for walking. Dungarvan is a lovely old market town, with lots of good restaurants and pubs.The Bay is home to a large oyster fishery, and a favourite walk is out to the Connager, a shingle spit that stretches three miles across the bay; it is a protected habitat with many rare species, such as the horned poppy. The Comeragh Mountains are a walkers paradise, with many scenic attractions, such as Mahon Waterfall.
Helvick Head and Ardmore, an Early Christian site, with a dramatically located Round Tower, are just a few minutes drive away. A little further along the coast you will find Youghal, an ancient walled town. Lismore, with its Castle and Gardens, and Cappoquin are historic villages on the Blackwater River, a fisherman
host_about: Hi there, my name is Tom , I live in Dublin with my family.  We both enjoy going for hikes in the mountains, forests and walks along the nearby beaches. We also love our holiday home in Dungarvan Co Waterford,which has a wonderful selection of very good restaurants, pubs, music and the fantastic Greewway Cycle Path.

name: Cottage with Spectacular Waterfront Views
description: A Breathtaking Connemara landscape right on your doorstep in the authentic Gaeltacht (Irish Speaking) region.  Once the teacher's residence of the adjoining tiny schoolhouse, the house is equipped for modern living but still maintains an old time charm.  A quiet and amazingly beautiful retreat away from the tourist traps. You can enjoy a wonderful relaxing time to eat,drink or schedule a massage (see info)  in our new heated conservatory with amazing views of Casheen Bay.
neighborhood_overview:
The location is unique and authentic and you will be right in the heart of the Irish Speaking Community. You will see the locals on curraghs (traditional boats) collecting sea weed and hand fishing for mackerel and hear their stories.

Depending o the time of year you can burn wood or turf on the fire or sit outside and take in the views. Aran Islands are only ten miles away by sea. There are numerous coves, beaches and inlets to explore along the rugged coastline, in addition to great opportunities for sailing, fishing and scuba diving. Children from all around Ireland come to stay in houses in this community during the summer months to learn the language so you may notice them on your walks. There are two bikes available if you wish to cycle the winding roads of Cnoc down to Tra Ban (white beach) or you could venture to Carraroe the nearest village if you are missing a supermarket!

Golf Anyone? Connemara Isles Golf Club is located in close by Lettermore.
host_about: Angela and Gerry are both from Dublin but have spent many years in New York City and now Florida.  They travel back and forth across the Atlantic to enjoy the best of both worlds.  While they are not in Ireland, many people get to enjoy their little yellow house in Lettermullen by the sea.  Angela is a retired school principal and was charmed by the fact that the house was the residence of the local school teacher of the small school that it adjoins.  Gerry is a retired plumber and a keen sailor.  He also loves their traditional curragh that he uses to catch mackerel with a hand line when they visit their house in the off season. They are fortunate to have great friends/neighbors such as Paraic and Vanessa who act as hosts during the times when they are not there.

name: Clare Ecolodge, ideal for group get-togethers.
description: Clare Ecolodge is an historic house and has been in the Loughnane family for over 100 years. While being located in the centre of a small village there is a  12 acre farm which give guests the feeling of being in the middle of the countryside. The best of both worlds. Groups are invited to book the entire premises. Lots of quiet walking and cycling routes. Good pubs, friendly community. 10 minutes from Lough Derg, 20 mins to Ennis, 45 mins to Shannon airport.
neighborhood_overview:
Clare Ecolodge is an ideal location from which to discover the Mid West and Western region of Ireland. We are close to the Wild Atlantic Way (30 to 40 minutes). East Clare has it's own charm and is steeped in history and heritage, the area is known for walkways, cycling routes with quiet roads, stunning lakes, the rugged Slieve Aughty mountains and of course its vibrant Irish traditional music scene.

We are located just 20 minutes from both Ennis and Killaloe and less than an hour to the Cliffs of Moher, Limerick and Galway. Clare Ecolodge is on a 12 acre farm and offers a unique blend of tranquility and easy going fun, giving guests a genuine rural Ireland experience.
host_about:
Clare Ecolodge has two properties. One in the centre of Galway and one in the heart of East Clare in the small rural village of Feakle.

At Clare Ecolodge in East Clare we offer group accommodation for tours and space for residential courses. The building, which has been in the family for over 100 years, was renovated and reopened in 2000.  Since then we have been welcoming guests from all over the world. Clare Ecolodge is on a 15 acre farm and offers a unique blend of tranquility and easy going fun giving guests a genuine rural Irish experience. 
Feakle is an ideal location from which to discover the Mid West and Western region of Ireland. East Clare is steeped in history and heritage.  The area is known for walkways, stunning lakes, the rugged Slieve Aughty mountains and of course its vibrant Irish traditional music scene. 
We are located just 20 minutes from both Ennis and Killaloe and less than an hour to the Cliffs of Moher and Galway. 

Our house in Galway speaks for itself. It is big and lovely and it’s central location could not be better. 

Thanks to all our Airbnb guests. We have had nothing but positive experiences and look forward to many more.

name: Cosy double in Eclectic Arty home, near Guinness
description:
Comfortable double bed with breakfast in our centrally located home, which we will be sharing with you. Our home is full of our personality which we enjoy sharing with guests.
8 minutes walk from Guinness, a 10 min bus ride will bring you into the heart of the city centre, or 25-30 min walk to the Trinity College entrance. Bus - 1 min, and tram - 8 mins walk from the house.
Booking: Please be aware of our CHECK-IN times, incl a photo & info in your profile, & your arrival times when booking.
neighborhood_overview:
The area of Dublin 8 is a local neighbourhood, near the city Centre. It is a residential area with a lidl supermarket, cafe, launderette, hairdresser and a pharmacy close by.
A ten minute walk will get you to some good bars and cafes, and a street for antiques, and a 10 minute bus, or 25 minute walk will get you into the heart of the city centre , with bars, restaurants, music, etc. Trinity College is another 5 mins.
Dublin city centre is relatively small so everything is very close and walkable. The bus is a minute away and the Luas (tram) is 8 minutes away fron the house.
We've compiled a list of places we like to go and a map for you to take away, bars, restaurants, etc, as well as a selection of touristy things if you'd prefer. The Guinness Brewery is a few minutes walk away ( you can see the bar at the top from our kitchen), Teelings Whiskey distillery, Christchurch and St.Patricks Cathedrals are 10-20 minutes walk away, and downtown bars and restaurants about 25 m
host_about:
Hi. We are Ayelet and Steve. We like living so close to the city centre, allowing us to walk or cycle everywhere. We also enjoy traveling when we can, and always seem to bring something back with us. 
We're really enjoying the experience of meeting new people with Airbnb, and always look forward to meeting more.
When you contact us, please tell us a little something something about yourselves, we would really appreciate it.

host_about: I have been living here in Ireland for the last 24 years.  Six years ago we sold our business and are semi-retired. We love to read books and have a original band with three other members and we gig regularly.  Our motto is to enjoy life and every day that comes your way.
