name: Unique private retreat in nature-tranquil setting
description:
A beautifully converted bus set in quiet rural surroundings 2.4 miles from Feakle, a village in County Clare, Ireland. A lovely comfortable experience with everything you need to hand.
Perfect access to East Clare walking routes and nearby lakes , a short distance to the 'Wild Atlantic Way'.The Beautiful Burren landscape is only a 30 min drive where turloughs and hazel coppices abound. A turlough is a type of disappearing lake found mostly in limestone areas

Peace and tranquility surround
neighborhood_overview:
Peace and tranquility resides in this area. There are numerous local lakes and east Clare walks to enjoy.
Walking routes (East Clare Walk Ways) and lakes (Lough Derg, Graney, Ea)

East Clare golf course is nearby.

There is easy access to the Burren which is an area of outstanding beauty and which i would highly recommend visiting while in the locality.

The Traditional Feakle Music festival is from 6-9th August in the nearby village, This is operating in a limited capacity this year, but due to the high demand of accommodation during this time and the limited accommodation available in the area, i can only accept bookings for a minimum of 4 nights during this period.
host_about:
I live near the village of feakle and spend alot of my time working on the land and garden creating various new projects as i go.
I am a visual artist with my emphasis on photography but also work with other artists on collaborations and inspired projects.

name: Eagles Rock Cottage - Beautiful Isolation
description:
Eagles Rock Cottage is a cosy, spacious and comfortable retreat in the mountains overlooking the picturesque Glenade valley. The original 100 yr old cottage has been fully renovated. It is the perfect location for those looking for a private, quiet, get away. Perfect for a romantic weekend or hill walking adventure.

We accept bookings for a minimum of 7-nights only. Check in/out is a Saturday
neighborhood_overview:
The village of Kinlough is 10 minutes by car and the coast is reachable in 15 minutes. The towns of Donegal, Sligo and Enniskillen are within easy reach (30min, 25mins and 1 hr respectively), so exploration of Donegal, Sligo, Leitrim and Fermanagh is all possible.

The location of Eagles Rock Cottage is perfect for any number of outdoor activities. It is situated 300m from the start of the Eagles Rock trail, a trail that takes the walker onto Trusc Mór for fabulous views of Glenade and Donegal Bay. It is the perfect location for:

Hillwalking - through the Darty mountains
Cycling - through the quiet country roads
Fishing - course fishing in Glenade Lake and Salmon and Trout by license in the Drowse
Surfing - at Bundoran off the beach, or off 'The Peak'
Nature Photography and Painting- around the cottage and general Glenade area.

Of course if you just want to get away from it all there is a well stocked library of books for quiet hours
host_about: We are a family of five, we have three young boys who keep us on our toes. We love to travel and explore new areas and to see places as the locals would see them. Likewise we are pleased to help any guest who are travelling to our locality.

name: Artists' Cottage @ Multi Award-Winning Cnoc Suain
description:
''A place quite unlike any other'' The Guardian.

Welcome to Cnoc Suain, our family-owned hillside settlement nestled within an enchanting rural landscape in the Gaeltacht region of Connemara.

Located on a popular cycling route between two villages: Spiddal(6.5km) for beach, crafts & music, and Moycullen(8.5km) for Friday farmers market & adventure centre. Only 25 mins drive from Galway City (Ireland's cultural capital) yet fully immersed in the wild beauty of Connemara.
neighborhood_overview:
The cottage is 6km from the coastline, on the Wild Atlantic Way. It is a 25-minute drive/20 km from Galway City (via Moycullen village), Ireland’s cultural capital.

It is located in a rural countryside setting and situated in the Conamara Gaeltacht (Irish/Gaelic speaking region) on the Mountain Road between the villages of An Spidéal (Spiddal) and Maigh Cuilinn (Moycullen). An Baile Íochtar (The Lower Village) on the property is immersed in the tranquil surrounds of Cnoc Suain’s privately owned 200-acre nature preserve.

There are neighbouring farms with cattle and sheep.

The picturesque coastal fishing village of An Spidéal (Spiddal) has two beaches and piers, a scenic coastal walk, craft village & café, pubs, restaurant, takeaways, takeaway coffee, pharmacy, medical centre and small supermarket & gas station, and is a 9-minute (6.5km) drive from Cnoc Suain.

The village of Maigh Cuilinn (Moycullen) is situated near the Corrib Lake. Artisan
host_about:
Hello, and welcome to our home, Cnoc Suain, a hillside settlement in the Connemara Gaeltacht.

My name is Dearbhaill, and I am a musician, teacher, and native Gaelic speaker from Connemara. My husband, Charlie, is a natural scientist and teacher from Dublin.

The combined passion we share for the culture and nature of Connemara has been our inspiration throughout the restoration of this settlement and experiences we offer. 

We can happily recommend places, events, activities, and experiences – both well known and lesser known – that bring you to the heart of the culture of the area. 

We have received national and international recognition for our cultural programmes, environmental stewardship, and restoration work. Awards Cnoc Suain has won include a "Global Vision Award" from Travel + Leisure magazine and a "World Ethical Travel Award" from The Guardian newspaper. After winning the Irish award for Cultural Heritage at the Irish Centre for Responsible Tourism Awards held in Dublin in March 2015, Cnoc Suain later won a world award for Cultural Heritage at the World Responsible Tourism Awards held in London in November 2015.

In 2017, Cnoc Suain was judged as Ireland's "Best Cultural Experience" by the Irish Tourism Industry Awards.

We look forward to having you stay! 

Le dea-ghuí,

Dearbhaill & Charlie

name: Stunning Seaside Designer Home, Sleeps 9, Donegal
description:
Welcome to our impressive home with panoramic sea views, this stunning summer house is located on an elevated site on the Wild Atlantic Way,. The property is finished to the highest standard boasting a first floor open plan living area complete with a sun room overlooking the sea. 4 bedroom property 1.5 miles from the sea.
Donegal was voted by National Geographic as the number 1 place to go in the world on their 'COOL LIST' (Dec 1st 2016) - ‘A wild dreamlike landscape’.
neighborhood_overview:
Up the road right and keep right is the spectacular headland of Bloody Foreland (named for the crimson colour of the rocks at sunset on the sea)

Visit Horn Head and Glenveagh national park, with 16000 hectares of mountains, lakes, wood and bog. Glenveagh contains the largest red dear population in Europe. The castle and gardens are worth visiting alone for a breathtaking insight to times gone by.

Visit Dunlewey Lakeside Centre- facilities include restaurant, tea-room, craft shop, adventure play area, pets and animals, story telling, boat trips on Dunlewey lake, guided tours and weaving demonstrations

Take a day trip to Tory Island or Gola Island. The ferry service is available from Bunbeg or Magheraroarty harbour several times a day.

Climb Errigal and Muckish. Mount Errigal is the highest mountain in Donegal with more fun descending than climbing.

Fishing, Golf, Traditional Music 1 mile. Walking. Horse riding, Swimming Pool 3 mile

name: The Black Gate Loft, Kilcrohane
description:
The Black Gate Loft is a self catering accommodation situated in the recently renovated community owned Alice West Centre which is located on the picturesque, peaceful and unspoilt Sheep’s Head peninsula in West Cork.

PRICE:
€60.00 per night
neighborhood_overview: community spirit,  there is always something going on especially in the summer.... the criac in the local pubs is great.
host_about:
Hi there Airbnb guests,

We are the Community Council for the Sheeps head/Kilcrohane/Ahakista and surrounding areas.  You will mostly will be dealing me  Annette  who  works part time for the community.  The funds from the Airbnb rentals will go towards upkeep building and fund lots of community projects such as the older peoples social club, Kids/family Easter egg hunt,  Youth groups etc.


Hi my name is Annette,
 
I am married with 3 children. I moved to the area about 12 years ago, and fell in love with the area as well as a local man....   I work with the local Community Council and my colleague Eileen O'Mahony and I manage the loft accommodation on behalf of the Community Council.  We are part of a great team of people who strive to promote our area and to provide community services for all ages within our local rural community.   

All the proceeds from Airbnb are invested back into the local community.  Money is used to maintain the Alice West Centre and to support local community council projects throughout the year. 

When I have some spare time, I try to indulge my love of music, both Irish and County music.  I am part of a group of Set Dancers that compete in local and national dancing competitions and I am also a member of the local church choir.  

I love meeting new people and thoroughly enjoy when people come to stay with us at the Blackgate.  It is nice to meet people from other parts of the county and from all over the world.  Everyone has their own story, some come to get away from work, some to catch up with the family, and others like to take some time out to clear their head and explore the beautiful area of West Cork. 

People love the peace and quiet the place has to offer. 

I look forward to meeting many more people via Airbnb.  See you soon.

Annette

neighborhood_overview:
Dungarvan is a beautiful coastal town, with a marina and it is surrounded by the Knockmealdown and Comeragh mountains.

It has a number of fantastic restaurants, pubs and coffee shops and has a great reputation for artisan foods.

The beach is just 2 miles outside of town for building sandcastles, paddling and swimming. There are two playgrounds, tennis courts and a bowling green. There are 9 championship golf courses in Co Waterford with 3 in Dungarvan alone. The Waterford Greenway is a cycle way from Dungarvan to Waterford which is suitable for young and old and is off-road so very safe. The start is a 5 minute cycle from the house

The Co Waterford Gaeltacht just outside town ensures Dungarvan is a great place for traditional music, language and culture. The historic towns of Ardmore and Lismore are 15 minutes drive.

For those taking longer breaks, Dungarvan is also a great spot to take a day trip to Waterford, Kilkenny and Cork City.
host_about:
I have 3 boys aged 26, 22 and 18. 
I am originally from Dublin but now  living in Co Waterford. I spent 23 years working in the Pharmaceutical Industry eventually getting to Director level and I have now packed in the corporate world to enjoy life - in the beautiful Co Waterford countryside looking at the Atlantic Ocean.
 I love all sorts of music,  art, antiques, travelling - learning about different cultures and foods

neighborhood_overview:
The house is wonderfully located within the town and 500 yards from the beautiful River Moy. A five minute stroll along the river brings you into the town centre, where there are many traditional shops, bars and restaurants showcasing some of our fabulous local produce. Just a stones throw from the house is the wonderful town park, with basketball & tennis courts (grass & tarmac) and a great children's adventure playground. The town is also host to the Jackie Clarke Collection, Ireland's most important collection of historical material from the last 4 centuries. Over 100,000 items are housed in the musuem.... a wonderful place to visit!

name: Kim's House
description: Our home is bright and family friendly with a good space downstairs and a main bedroom and 2 children's bedrooms (for 3 kids) upstairs.
host_about: I'm a friendly, honest, easygoing person who loves to travel and experience what life has to offer. name: Beautiful spacious Farmhouse with stunning views
description: Bayfield is a beautifully restored 6 bed 5 bath farmhouse situated in its own 3 acres of gardens, orchard and rough land looking out over Galway Bay. It is right on one of the loveliest parts of the Wild Atlantic Way. It has stunning views over the Bay to Galway and the hills of the Burren National Park are all around.
neighborhood_overview:
There is an endless supply of things to do in the area. The walks are top of the list for most people. The coastal walk offers different scenery every time you walk it due to the ever changing height of tide. At low tide the rock pools are great for foraging in for sea life and the local sandy beach extends out into Galway Bay. Quite often seals bask on the rocks of nearby inlets. The walks in the limestone covered hills that surround New Quay are also brilliant. There are easy walks and also some more challenging circuits that you won’t want to try unless you are fairly fit and take some provisions for. There are several horse riding stables in the area and quite often horse racing or point to point racing which is very popular in Ireland.

The local villages of Kinvara and Ballyvaughan are great to visit and have superb pubs and restaurants. They often host festivals and regularly have live Irish music being played in one or other of the pubs. Further afield is Galway whic

At one end of the street is a little walkway to the river bank - then over the footbridge into Dartry park - great for jogging, dog walking or just strolling among the tall trees - turn left to the weir where you can stand and watch the herons and cormorants drying their wings.  Keep walking straight on beside the river to the bridge, turn right and continue up the hill to the buzzing neighbourhood of Rathgar with its Supermarket, coffee shops and restaurants.  Or you can carry on  through the next park and further along the banks of the Dodder, full of wild life. The other direction brings you to the famous Dropping Well Pub - all of 5 minutes from my home!  Walk through the park and just past the Dropping Well Pub - first left at the railway bridge -  to the Luas Tram. St Stephens Green is only 10 minutes away, or continue walking along the river a
host_about: I really enjoy lots of things!  Cooking, ethnic food, live music, singing, walking, the countryside, movies, reading, vintage shops and markets, travelling when I can - especially to France where I try to speak as much French as possible!  I'd love to travel more - who knows where I might end up!  And of course - meeting people from anywhere and everywhere!

name: Exquisitely restored Victorian Flat - WB Yeats
description:
A wonderfully bright and spacious apartment that can sleep up to 6 people comfortably.

Located on the 2nd floor it has many of the original features that were common in the Victorian era. Complete with a marble fireplace & a large bay window overlooking the city of Dublin as well as beautiful coving on high ceilings giving a great sense of space and oppulence.

Situated just 3 min walk from supermarket, pubs and restaurants 10 min walk, Phoenix Park 8 min walk.

Fully equipped kitchen
neighborhood_overview:
This street is a beautifully tree lined street which runs right up the the entrance of the Phoenix Park.
This park is the largest urban park in Europe and houses Dublin Zoo and the presidential home and offices as well as a children's playground. It is a wonderful park to visit and spans over 1750 acres.
The street also has beautiful Victorian red bricked houses all along it which date back to the 18th century so it really is a taste of old Dublin.
There is a major supermarket just 2 minutes walk as well as a pharmacy, bakery, coffee shops, bars, restuarants and many other amenities all within easy walking distance.
host_about: I grew up in the tourist business as my parents ran a hotel in Kildare so I have always wanted to get back into the hosptality industry.  I have owned this house from the early '90's when I returned from New York where I had lived for a number of years.  I have been in the buidling trade for the last 20 years so I thought I would combine the two and refurbish the house and provide rental accommodation in an extremely convenient locations to tourists.

name: Blackstairs Courtyard Cottage, South Co Carlow
description:
Self-contained stone cottage attached to our 200 year-old farm-house. Double-height living room with excellent piano, wood-burning stove, small sunny kitchen, upstairs gallery with double bed and full bathroom off it, south-facing French windows to terrace and gardens. Gay-friendly, and a very peaceful, beautiful place, between the Blackstairs Mountains and the River Barrow.
Two nights minimum stay. Not suitable for children or pets.
We follow Airbnb’s five-step enhanced cleaning process.
neighborhood_overview:
We are 5km and 8km respectively from the lovely villages of Graignamanagh, Co Kilkenny and Borris, Co Carlow, where you will find shops, pubs and restaurants. Beautiful St Mullins, with its monastic ruins, Norman motte and excellent café on the river, is 8km away. We are 36km from Kilkenny City and 40km from Carlow Town, for restaurants, shopping, art galleries, theatre and cinemas.
There are lovely walks in the Blackstairs and along the Barrow, and great swimming in the river Barrow at Clashganny, 3km away, and St Mullins. There are bicycles for hire in Graiguenamanagh and kayaking is also available.
host_about:
Originally from London, I've lived in Ireland since 1986. My partner Deborah and I moved to Blackstairs Courtyard in 2001 when it had lain empty and ruined for 37 years. We love this life, making new gardens, growing delicious food, welcoming family and friends to share this magical space. 
I am a jazz musician, still doing gigs, making albums and loving life.

name: The Penthouse Apt at Harveys Dock
description:
This spacious two bedroom, two bathroom luxury penthouse suite is fabulously decorated. Right in the heart of the historic walled town of Youghal, Co. Cork and walking distance to amenities, ample parking. Great spot to explore the South of Ireland.

**This apartment is also suitable for isolating as it has a large private balcony.
neighborhood_overview:
Youghal is a Historical Seaside town half an hour from Cork City. It located in the very centre of The Irish Riviera. The fantastic beaches are it's greatest attraction, but there's so much more to see and do, for all ages, all year round, and.

Youghal, and the surrounding area, are a year round holiday destination for families, friends, the energetic and those seeking relaxation, and there is a wide variety of things to do too. Youghal to Midleton Greenway and Youghal Beach Board Walk are within easy walking range.

Steeped in history, and blessed with beautiful countryside, lots of things to see and do, and beaches all around. Lots of outdoor activities available locally including boat trips, fishing, diving,sailing & golf. Famous Jameson distillery 15 minutes drive. Ballymaloe house and cookery school 30 minutes drive. Cliff house hotel Ardmore 15 minutes. Ballynatray house 10 minutes.
host_about: I've been in the hospitality industry for over 40 years, involved in hotel accommodation and restaurant. I am part of the team that run Ahernes Seafood Bar in Youghal . A family business since 1923 .Please give me a call or email if you've any questions, I have lots of local knowledge to give you ideas on where to visit from local beaches to well known tourist attractions.

Set in the beautiful surroundings of a 19th century former rectory over looking Cork Harbour, a true oasis of peace and calm where time seems to standstill.

host_about: I am a Registered Nurse Acupuncturist & Homoeopath and in 2005 I founded a natural healing and wellness Sanctuary in a beautiful Grade 2 listed Victorian House, Robin Hill House,  in Cobh Co Cork Ireland. We would love to welcome you to Robin Hill Sanctuary.

name: City Centre Apartment, sleeps 2
description: Location! Location! Location! You couldn't be more central in our comfortable 1 bed apartment. Only 500m from O'Connell St with all major transport links, cafes & shops and Dublin's most famous tourist hotspots  less than 5mins from the front door.
neighborhood_overview: Location, location, location! Bachelors Walk is a very lively city centre location with lots of shops, restaurants, cafes, bars & night-life right outside your door! If you don't mind the hustle & bustle associated with city centre living then this is the perfect spot to get to visit and experience the many sights and sounds of Dublin. name: Lovely Apartment In Middle Of Town
description:
A gorgeous brand new architecturally designed two-bedroom apartment is in the center of Dingle town
Central location but nice and quiet.
There are Original artworks on the walls.
It's a Cosy clean and modern with character. Great location to explore dingle town and the beautiful dingle peninsula.
Two Double bedrooms with Feather Duvet and a Separate kitchen living room and modern bathroom.
Our shop is just below so you can ask us if you need anything
Easy Free parking.
neighborhood_overview:
Dingle is a great little town and our flat is right in the middle of it. Around 5min walk to the famous Dick Macs pub, lots of great top class restaurants close by, a very nice bakery around the corner + few take aways down the road.

Dingle Town has some great shopping. Our own shop is rather good ! The flat is above the shop. Look up kathleen mcauliffe online. Discount of 10% for Airbnb guests.

Dingle has a pier an aquarium a climbing wall lots of boat trips to see great variety of wild life whales dolphins magical islands.
The landscape around dingle is fantastic. National geographic said it was one of the most beautiful places on earth. It is a great place to come for clean healthy fun walking windsurfing surfing horse riding all nearby. Slea head drive you will see ancient beehive huts and ruins of castles to explore.
A great flat in friendly beautiful location céad míle fáilte (a hundred thousand welcomes)
host_about:
I have been living in the Dingle area for the past 26 years. For work I am a Accessory Designer. I mainly make hats.and Jewllery  If you (Hidden by Airbnb) my name you will find my company site and lots of info.  
 
Love the area and being outside. Have great local knowledge of hill walking and cycling round Dingle. When I find time i paint which is what i studied at collage. Husband Niall and son Finn are very into Surfing and windsurfing in the Dingle area and will happily pass on where when to go. 

Dingle a great place to eat,drink and shop and after much testing ! have all the tips you could need for a good stay.

Airbnb is such a great thing. Have had great experiences all over the world using it . I use it all the time . So much nicer than a Hotel.

name: Glenlohane Cottage - Gateway The Scenic Southwest
description:
Built in the 1600's and added onto over the years, the exquisite Glenlohane Cottage is surrounded by 250 acres of the farm/estate Glenlohane Country House, a prestigious Hidden Ireland Private Guest House B&B.
Saturday - Saturday rental 945/week.
As of 7/7/20, a two-week quarantine for all non-resident visitors is required and remains in place until we as a nation are told differently.
This cottage is not suitable for young children.
neighborhood_overview: One of the greatest take-always that guests tell us about from their stay is simply going into our little town, Kanturk. Our neighbors and townsfolk are just super nice, friendly and are inquisitive about who you are and where you are from and what you think. See our historical Kanturk Castle - it's rather amazing in a land of castles. Blarney is only 1/2 an hour away, Cork City 45 minutes, Kenmare and Kinsale only an hour and a half, Lismore and it's castle and gardens just less than that, Killarney 45 minutes and Muckross House and the lakes are worth a day. We have tons of trips we do ourselves and they are all within easy reach. Who knew Kanturk was so well situated???!
host_about:
As the 10th generation living at Glenlohane, I came over from Virginia three  years ago to help my parents with our farm/estate. As Glenlohane is Bord Failte approved and a part of the prestigious Hidden Ireland, you may find us easily on the web from anywhere.

My family and I grew up mostly in Connecticut but Dad was born here on the farm, studied in America, did his stint jumping out of planes for the US Air Force, then worked at Guinness in Dublin and in NYC. Both of my parents are active historians and are really interesting/fun to talk to - and they always make the time to chat with guests - and me if I'm lucky.

I also went away to school, then college, studied in Paris as well, and worked in Boston, Dublin, NYC and Richmond, Virginia before coming here. 

I do a lot of sailing/racing in Kinsale and Crosshaven. And...we are REALLY into vintage motorcycles. Thus, we have started a motorcycle touring business as we are probably the most ideally situated because of our knowledge/love of bikes, facilities and location standpoints - you will note this from the website if you care to look up Glenlohane Country House.

I have stayed in a few Airbnb destinations and it has been really great. This appears to be an exciting community of not only places to stay but also one appears to get to know the host(s) which is what we are all about anyhow.

Favorite Motto/Quote? 'Ulysses S. Grant Never Heard the Word Can't.'

name: Off Grid Eco Cabin Hideaway in pristine woodlands
description:
A fully immersive back-to-nature experience for kids, families and nature lovers. All self catering.

Our little eco-cabin is nestled at the edge of our farm property, right by a beautiful old-growth forest. Totally off-grid, this cabin has all the makings of a rustic, back-to-basics experience. The pace slows down, and your senses come alive again. It's the perfect place to unwind, explore, and remember how to live simply and joyfully.
neighborhood_overview:
Crann Óg Eco Farm is well situated for excursions to the Burren National Park, the Cliffs of Moher, the Wild Atlantic Way, Coole Park, Kilmacduagh Monastery and Thoor Ballyle, former home of W.B. Yeats.

Crann Óg Eco Farm is nestled between two native Irish woodlands and a stones throw from the mysterious Gort river, which disappears underground and re-appears seven times on it's way to Dunguaire Castle at Kinvarra. There are several lakes nearby, woodlands, rivers, and wonderful places to walk and cycle straight from the farm. (We can refer you to local bicycle rentals if you are interested and in need!) The lovely beach town of Kinvara is 25 min drive away.

We are 9km from the town of Gort and a 45 minutes drive away from Galway city and the town of Ennis.

The ancient monastic site of Kilmacduagh is only a 20min drive here.
host_about:
Crann Og Eco Farm - a place to be in nature. 
An Eco-holiday and retreat venue showcasing sustainable living.
On the doorstep of The Wild Atlantic Way, The Cliffs of Moher and The Burren National Park.

A quiet hideaway next to the woods..

Self-catering accommodation.
Off-grid with solar power usb ports to charge devices in wooden A-frame cabin. 
Compost toilets.

Walking / Cycling : seashore walks on site and locally. The now famous ‘Greenway’, the route of the old narrow gauge railway line that originally extended from Westport to Achill , has been transformed into a safe cycle/walkway/jogging route with over 30 miles of beautiful coastal countryside. The route passes within easy access of Croibh-inis House (approx 2km ) and extends through Newport onto Mulranny and finally to Achill.

Hill walking: The nearby Nephin mountains and the famous pilgrimage mountain of Croagh Patrick with its sister mountains and Western way will provide a challenge to hill walkers.

name: Best Views Wild Atlantic Way-Beautiful large house
description:
A large, beautiful house on the Wild Atlantic Way and scenic Ring of Kerry - fabulous views - all rooms are ensuite with WC & shower.

Fully equipped kitchen, utility room, TV/family room, dining room, and outdoor deck with BBQ.
Perfect for nature lovers, beaches, and walking. 10-minute drive from Kenmare, and a 20-minute drive to Sneem.
There are walks in the woods just opposite the house.
All bed linens, towels, and essentials are here for you.

New renovations were completed in February 2020.
neighborhood_overview: World Famous ring of kerry area, Set on the ring of kerry and the Kerry way. Close to beaches, mountains, walks and nature
host_about:
We are delighted to offer you a home from home on your travels here on The Ring of Kerry.  Our home offers spectacular views of Kenmare bay all the way out to the Atlantic Sea.  We are a family that enjoys hosting guests. We both enjoy travelling, reading, the area around us and making life fun. I live in the house with my Son Elliot (who is passionate about writing) who is 18 and our small dog Storm.  My mum lives separately in a Granny house at the back, so there are always people around to interact with and offer advice for both travel and the local area.  
We love to travel and we use Airbnb both as hosts and guests.  We love the experience of travelling through Airbnb as it offers us what we value most a home based, local experience while travelling.  i am a business and marketing graduate. We now work in furniture creation and retail and our home is furnished with some of our own unique furniture.

Our home provides a base from where you can explore the ring of Kerry or the Kerry area.  It is situated on Ireland's world famous Wild Atlantic way coastal route, that spans 7 of Ireland's counties along the West coast.

Our home offers a relaxed,comfortable and cozy space to explore this wonderful scenic area.  We really enjoy living in our home and we enjoy sharing the experience of our home with other travellers.

name: Beautiful 2 Bed Holiday Farmhouse
description: Stay in a beautifully restored 2 bed farmhouse in Ballylooby, Cahir, Co. Tipperary in the heart of the Golden Vale. Situated on a working farm, this 100 year old farmhouse comes full with Irish charm and character.
neighborhood_overview:
There are TONS of things to do in the area:

COUNTRYSIDE: Walk the Vee in the nearby Sugar Loaf mountains. The Vee is famous because of the breathtaking panoramic views afforded to travellers and sight seers going through the pass. The journey rises to about 2,000 feet (610m) above sea level above Bay Lough, and as it does so it gives wonderful views of a portion of the ‘Golden Vale’ between the Knockmealdown and Galtee Mountain Ranges.

RAMBLING: If walking is your thing, then the area around the Vee, Bay Lough, Loughglenbridge, Sugar Loaf Hill, Knockshanahullion and Gortacullen Wood (just under the Vee following the Tipperary Heritage Way sign) offer a multitude of choices no matter what type of road walking or mountain climbing you fancy. Take a look at our Walks section to give you an idea of some of your options.

HISTORY: Visit nearby Cahir Castle, one of the largest castles in Ireland, is sited on an island in the river Suir. It was built in 1142
host_about: I live outside Cahir, on a small farm in beautiful South Tipperary. It is my pleasure to welcome you to my restored Irish farmhouse. See you soon!

name: Historic Oasis - Heart Of Dublin
description:
Located in one of Dublin's most historic and central neighbourhoods, built in 1830 built around the Grand Canal, this private oasis is just a few minutes' walk from all of Dublin's most popular sites including Trinity College, St. Stephen's Green and Temple Bar.

You'll have everything you need to have a memorable and unique stay, with local coffee shops and restaurants located right across the street.
neighborhood_overview:
We live in historic Georgian Dublin. The house itself was built in the 1800's and still maintains many original features, with a modern twist.

The area is really charming just outside the city center. Just across the street there is a deli, Starbucks, convenience store, restaurants and traditional Irish pubs! There are also local parks and a canal with a nice walk on our street.

name: THE GLASSHOUSE
description: THE GLASSHOUSE - set on the slope of a hill, surrounded by green fields and with panoramic views over Inch Bay and the highest mountains of the island.
neighborhood_overview:
THE GLASSHOUSE is located just 1 km from the Dingle Way between the blue flag Inch Beach and the historic village of Annascaul. Inch Beach- a 5 minute drive from THE GLASSHOUSE -with its beautiful stretch of dunes 5 km into the sea offers a variety of activities, from watersports to walks. There is a surf school and a restaurant , serving delicious local produce right on the beach. The lovely local pub - Foley's Bar - is just a short drive past Inch Beach.
The pittoresque town of Dingle with its unique pubs and award winning restaurants is a 20 minute drive away. The nearby village of Annascaul is 4 km inland and offers several nice pubs, 1 shops, a post office and a cafe. The surrounding of Annascaul Lake with its magnific mountain scenery is perfect for walking tours.The busy tourist town of Killarney is a 45 minute drive away.For walks, cycling tours or boat trips on the lakes the National Park is a must see.
The location of THE GLASSHOUSE is an ideal base from which to ex
host_about:
Some years ago my husband Peter and I made the decision to start a bed & breakfast business in our family home THE GLASSHOUSE.
We have been visiting the Dingle peninsula on holiday for more than 30 years and our love for this beautiful part of the country has led us to now make it our home full time.
Our unique home was built 20 years ago and was designed by myself to accomodate family and friends who shared our love for the house and the area. We hope you will come as a stranger and leave as a friend.

name: Fuchsia Lane
description: Perfect for two people (and base price includes two people), this lovely stone cottage is a peaceful haven.  You'll be sleeping in a loft bedroom, while the spacious open plan living area is perfect for cosy evenings in.  Add a sunroom with wonderful views over Dunmanus Bay, and you have the ideal spot to explore all that Schull and West Cork have to offer.
neighborhood_overview:
The cottage is 4 miles/6.5 km west of Schull, which is on the Wild Atlantic Way. We're close to beautiful sandy beaches and the extraordinary walks of Barleycove, Mizen Head, Sheep's Head and Three Castles Head, but there are also gorgeous local walks on the network of small roads around the house. There's very little traffic but you may have to make way for the occasional cow!

You'll be spoilt for choice for things to do around Schull. Some of our favourites are Schull Farmers' Market on Sunday morning; a walk (or bike ride) to Ballyrisode for a swim - or to our secret favourite beach, only revealed to guests! Schull boasts more than its fair share of boutique-style shops, like Enibas for jewellery, Pebbles for fab Irish knits, and a great bookshop where you can sip coffee as you browse. You can book a day of sailing or kayaking at fairly short notice. Then a Friday evening exhibition opening at the Blue House Gallery - a great opportunity to meet local artists and art
host_about: I live close to the furthest SW corner of Ireland.  I'm a keen gardener, walker, reader and swimmer in the cold sea.  As a guest I'm  fairly quiet and like to leave accommodation as if I hadn't been there.  Holidays tend to be in warm places or in lively cities - the opposites of where I live.  I aim to be a hospitable and friendly host, while guarding our guests' peace and privacy as our neighbours across the yard.

name: Retreat, 1 Mile from Dingle Town
description: Nature on your doorstep, mountains and sea, just one mile from the centre of Dingle Town, this is an ideal location to rest and relax. This double ensuite room in our family home is a good base from where to explore and enjoy the Dingle Peninsula.
neighborhood_overview: Dingle town centre is a 2 minute drive or a 15 minute walk. Dingle is a place the Irish love to visit, a town full of artists, musicians and writers who come from all over the world. A town full of brightly coloured houses and beautiful fresh food from the surrounding sea and landscape. Traditional pubs with real life Irish music sessions, the real Ireland. The Dingle Peninsula an Irish speaking area,  a magnificent landscape where the rugged mountains roll into the atlantic ocean. A place to walk, bike or take a boat trip. A place rich with ancient history and pre-historic sites that will leave you hungry for more.

name: Extraordinary, Off-Grid  Donegal Cottage
description: Just three minute’s walk to the Atlantic Ocean , our charming, rough little cottage sits alone in an iconic location, above the wild, smooth-stoned beach and tiny harbour of An Port, Donegal. It is a brilliant hideaway in a breath-taking landscape.
neighborhood_overview:
This is probably the most remote and beautiful stretch of coastline in Ireland , tho' I say it myself. (Actually lots of guide books say it too).
The cottage is the last inhabitable house on the coastline between Glencolmkille and Ardara.
The American artist Rockwell Kent came here to capture the raw Atlantic lifestyle of the people in the 1930's ; Dylan Thomas came here to dry out ...unsuccessfully , but wrote some of his most atmospheric poems over the hill in the abandoned studio at Glenlough .
Bonnie Prince Charlie is said to have sailed for Europe from here after escaping Scotland following his defeat at the battle of Culloden.
Shipwrecks, myths and legends abound .
host_about: now living in County Meath, Ireland -  and have travelled /lived all over - but mostly East Africa.

Here at BRANDYLOCHS COUNRTY HOUSE we can assure you of peace, privacy and superb access to all of what Kenmare has to offer. We are located simply 100 yards from the centre of town , yet in a quiet wooded area and not overlooked.

Kenmare and in particular the LODGE WOOD AREA offers you the chance to experience all that is great in what IRELAND has to offer.

name: Cozy Cottage with breathtaking views in Connemara
description: This cottage has been in our family for more than a generation - it boasts stunning views over Lough Mask and offers a beautiful space for up to 6 persons - families, fishermen, and outdoor enthusiasts will all have a great time here! The Cottage is located outside the village of Clonbur, in beautiful Connemara. Enclosed in pristine nature, the lush grassland, its stone walls, hills, mountains, as well as two of the largest lakes in Ireland invite you to relax and enjoy the house and nature.
neighborhood_overview: The cottage is situated outside the village of Clonbur within rural Irish structures. It’s very close to some unbelievable scenery and hikes, and the surrounding towns have all the provisions and hospitality to make your stay even more spectacular. You will be sufficiently far away from anyone to enjoy your free time but still close enough to walk down to the local pub. You can walk up the winding roads from the cottage, towards Mount Gable, and you are unlikely to see another tourist, maybe just one of the friendly, farmer neighbours who are all extremely friendly, open and helpful people.
host_about: Interested in culture, arts, history - and travel!

name: Burren Glamping -cosy & comfortable & quirky
description: A quirky and cosy converted horse truck on a  traditional Irish farm in The Burren, Co Clare, just off the Wild Atlantic Way, near the Cliffs of Moher, The Aran Islands and Galway City.  Sleeps 5 people comfortably,  but can make room for a 6th person with a little bit of a juggle. Warm and bright inside. The Burren is a unique place where you can enjoy spectacular geology, archaeology, scenery, history and heritage and music traditions. Kilfenora is the home of ceili music, steeped in tradition
neighborhood_overview:
We are situated in The Burren and Cliffs of Moher Geopark, outside the village of Kilfenora and enjoy scenic and peaceful countryside. The Glamping Truck sits right at heart of the farm, a stone throw from the well preserved Iron Age, Tullagh Ringfort. The lack of light pollution allows you to star gaze and the darkness at night allows for a good nights sleep.
The Burren, sometimes referred to as the fertile rock, is a part of the Wild Atlantic Way on the west coast of Ireland. It has a unique flora where Alpine, Arctic and Mediterranean plants grow side by side and the largest and most accessible karst regions in the world, with stunning geological formations and archaeological remains. Situated on the edge of the Burren, amongst rich grasslands, we run a traditional, sustainable and eco friendly farm, using no fertilizers or pesticides where animal welfare is core. We are part of the Burren Ecotourism Network and the Burren and Cliffs of Moher Geopark. In 2016 we won the prestig
host_about: Stephen (my husband) and I live in the beautiful Burren, a Global UNESCO Geopark, which is a unique limestone area on the west coast of Ireland. We run a small sustainable farm with rare breed pigs, cows, donkeys, chickens, hens, a couple of dogs and a cat. We are surrounded by archaeological remains and rolling green hills. We love the peaceful and quiet area we live in and appreciate how lucky we are to be in a place which is so special. We have an iron age ring fort next to our farm and when out working in the garden and you pick up a funny shaped stone, you wonder -  was this a prehistoric tool of some sort? Apart from living on the farm, we love meeting people from different cultures. Since we have to stay at home to look after all the animals, offering airbnb is a fantastic way of meeting interesting people from all over the world.

name: The Wonderly Wagon, cosy and snug all year round
description:
Step back in time and experience something very unique: A traditional bow top gypsy caravan set in a woodland in the Donegal hills totally off the beaten track. Lovingly restored to a high standard you feel cosy and snug in the midst of nature.
Please notice: The wagon can host no more than to 2 adults and additionally up to 2 children. Please carefully read the description before you book!
neighborhood_overview:
We live about 5km outside the village of Fintown and are linked via a mountainous back-road to the picturesque town of Glenties (half an hour drive). We are surrounded by forests, lakes, streams and rivers on the foot of Aghla mountain. We are located right beside a waymarked walking way called "The Gaeltacht/Sli na Finne Way", which makes it a great place for walking and exploring including lots of other walks and ways right at your doorstep. About half an hours drive from us we have several stunning beaches. The highest cliffs of Europe are nearby as well as Glenveagh National Park.
This is also an area well renowned for traditional music. Some famous fiddlers are living nearby and you will find regular traditional music sessions especially in the Glenties area.
host_about:
Hello, we are a family of 4: Declan + Marion with our two children.
We loved our first experiences as Airbnb hosts with our B&B. We met so many wonderful people and it as was a joy and pleasure to invite each one of them to our home, to get to know them and to make them feel welcome. That's what we want to continue to do.
With our first listing (Relax in the hills of Donegal) closed we now offer the following exciting listings: Our "Wonderly Wagon", a lovingly restored original bow-top gypsy caravan and our newly finished Meadowsweet Hill Lodge where you can either choose to book one of the two private rooms or the whole Lodge. We put all our passion into the self-build Lodge connected to our dream to own one day Ireland's smallest hostel. But it had to be so much more than a hostel where people meet and get together, it had to be something special and extra cosy! See for yourself!
We have often volunteers from all corners of the world staying with us in our home to help with different projects and in the garden. Our very next project will be to restore an old fishing boat into an accommodation with the theme of a pirate ship!
We all love and often play Irish traditional music together. I love and write poetry (one book published in Germany), I'm also a herbalist and a very keen gardener producing herbal tea's. Declan and I visited this area some years ago and fell straight in love with the nature, culture and people here. And now we simply want to share this beautiful experience with you!

name: House in the heart of Dublin
description: The movie stars choice! Central, stylish, calm and private house & garden between Dublin city centre and conveniently located, popular Camden St./Portobello area with private entrance. Sleeps 6 comfortably on 6 beds, 4/5 in 2 bedrooms + up to 6/7 including the living room, also ideal for 1 or a couple. Fireplace, large private deck out back for outdoor lunches, stocked kitchen/breakfast room for socialising. Modern-retro decor. Citywide recommendations provided. 5 star reviews. Look no further!
neighborhood_overview:
The house is situated at the edge of the bohemian Camden Street/Wexford Street and Portobello area but is also considered as 'South Inner-City' where most of the Dublin nightlife is. Synge Street is less than 10 minutes walking distance from Dublin's main shopping and restaurant district and cultural quarter surrounding Grafton Street.
Although only one block from the main street, Synge Street is surprisingly tranquil day and night.
Our neighbourhood is very central but offers a vibrant alternative to the regular Dublin tourist traps even though Temple Bar is a mere 15 minute walk away.
host_about:
A native Dub, fine-art graduate, working in the areas of music and design. I've been transforming my city centre, terraced house and garden for twenty years, creating a comfortable, relaxed style that mixes mid-century design with contemporary and Georgian features. I love city traveling most, cycling and walking to explore new places. I collect records, old and new.
Some favourite quotes:
“I travel a lot; I hate having my life disrupted by routine.” – Caskie Stinnett, travel writer
"Without question, the greatest invention in the history of mankind is beer. Oh, I grant you that the wheel was also a fine invention, but the wheel does not go nearly as well with pizza." – Dave Barry, American author

neighborhood_overview:

In my down time I cook, bake and spend enjoyable hours in my garden.

name: Luxurious log cabin Westport / Connemara
description:
Welcome to Eaglewood Lodge, a stunning handcrafted log cabin set deep in the scenic hills outside Westport. Built for connection, celebration, and escape, this unique retreat blends rustic beauty with modern luxury- offering the perfect setting for hen parties, stag weekends and family gatherings.

From the moment you arrive Eaglewood feels like a hidden gem. Surrounded by oak woods and rolling countryside it's a place where you can truly relax, be yourself, and enjoy the people you're with.

host_about:
Hi Im Michael

name: Eco studio near ring of Kerry
description:
Our small studio with its mini loft, fully equipped kitchen and wood stove will provide you with a cosy refuge after a day's trek or a trip to the sea.

We are located in a beautiful, tranquil and remote valley up a windy road at the foothills of mount Mangerton, 10 mins from the main Kenmare road.
The studio is across the yard from our family home and surrounded by a beautiful mature garden which you're welcome to explore. The studio contains a Bluetooth sound system and a washing machine.
neighborhood_overview:
We are at 5 km from the village in the middle of the Kerry mountains.
Mangerton stands right behind our house, it takes about 2 hours to reach the top where you are rewarded with a magnificent view of the region that stretches all the bay to Kenmare Bay and the Killarney Lakes in the other direction. On the summit, you will find two cavernous glacially formed lakes, one of which is the famous Devil's Punchbowl.
host_about: I am originally from France.  My husband Gerry and I have been living in the same house in the west of Ireland for quite a few years and continue to enjoy it.

name: Cosy coastal eco-cabin with stunning ocean views
description:
This snug, grass-roofed eco-cabin offers panoramic views of the Atlantic Ocean. Enjoy a warm Irish welcome, mountain walks on the Beara Way or snorkelling through nearby reefs. Sample local cheeses, lamb, fish and seafood or stoke up the wood-burning stove, have a glass of wine and and savour the peace and tranquillity!

Word of warning: we are VERY remote, (1km off the road down a rough track). With almost no public transport, own transport (eg car) is highly recommended - see Getting Around!
neighborhood_overview:
The wild and rugged landscape, spectacular, star-studded night sky and beautiful sunsets need to be seen to be believed. West Cork is truly a place apart.

You can sample local delicacies such as Mileens cheese, water buffalo burgers, free-range hen and duck eggs and pork sausages and the nearby town, Castletownbere, is Ireland's biggest white-fishing port so you can source fresh fish and shellfish at the SuperValu in Castletownbere.

There are regular music and set-dancing sessions at pubs in the area and there are art galleries and even a sculpture garden to visit. There is a ferry to Bere Island and Dursey Island, at the tip of the Beara Peninsula boasts Ireland's only Cable Car. But sometimes mooching around and exploring the teeming wildlife on the shoreline and in the rockpools is enough to keep you going.

Your hosts can tell you more and you can look at our visitor's book for ideas on things to see and do.
host_about:
Chatty, polylingual, intercultural communication trainer who loves to eat! Travel addict. Enjoy swimming, hiking, dogs, kids, beachcombing, flea-markets, playing pool, food foraging, theatre, cooking, movies - there's not much I'm not interested in.

As a host I am happy to recommend you interesting stuff to do or, (if I'm free), accompany you for a walk or a swim off the dock nearby. If  you prefer to explore on your own, or enjoy the peace and quiet in the hammock with a good book - outdoors if it's sunny or snuggled up in front of the fire if it's  stormy - then I'm quite happy to give you plenty of privacy. 

Live 2km from nearest other house and 10km from nearest settlement on the shore of the Atlantic Ocean in West Cork, Ireland where I beach-comb and forage for wild food obsessively. Very peaceful but it's nice to go somewhere there are other people from time to time. 

As a guest I don't need any babysitting, very able to entertain myself but like to mingle too.  Am very happy to do my own thing if the host needs peace and quiet.
neighbourhood: Gortagarriff, Kilcatherine, Eyeries, Beara, County Cork, Ireland

name: Surf view farmhouse cottage
description:
Overlooking Lahinch and Liscannor bay, just 5 minutes away from a surf or a round of golf in Lahinch, a music session in Doolin or a walk on the Cliffs of Moher, you will experience authentic Ireland at this lovely cosy renovated traditional cottage (Refurbished 2020-2022)
At Gwenn's, you don't get a hotel, you get a local experience. Gwenn will welcome you personally and help you to get the most of the area. Gwenn's cottage is truly a haven of peace and warm welcome.
neighborhood_overview:
The neighborhood is very friendly and peaceful.
What we love about living here on this hill is that we are 10 min away from busy little seaside towns of Lahinch and Doolin allowing us to deep in and out of the tourists buzz and amenities and yet return to absolute peace and quiet of the countryside surrounded by fields, horses, cows, bees buzzing and bird tweets.
host_about:
I'm originally from Brittany, France. 
I followed my passion for the Irish traditional flute to Ireland. Set to be a short stay of a few months, it has extended to become my country of adoption. I've been here over 20 years now, I've studied traditional Irish music, music technologies, played gigs and sessions all over Ireland and in many countries across the world . . Then I decided to settle in my favorite place in Ireland. I love county Clare. I nourish my soul of walks, runs, surfs, kayak trips and cycles around the Burren. I hunted a place where I would feel the wild Atlantic, where I would be surrounded by the sea and yet not too far from all amenities. This place is my dream come true. . .
It allowed me to delve even deeper in my passion for the wooden flute learning the art of flute making under the master guidance of Martin Doyle (www.martindoyleflutes.com) ..
For a few years, I delve into my other passions of health and fitness and qualified as a fitness instructor and a running technique specialist teaching the POSE methode ® of running. Setting up my own coaching business and pushed further afield looking into energy work while studying the tools of Access Consciousness.
I was also a tour guide for many years.
I am currently setting up my own workshop on the ground of the cottage and we will see what incredible creation will come out of it.
...
I believe in honesty, heart centered relationships, clear communication and following the exhilarating path of love and joy for life.
Good humour, belly laughs, adventures, witnessing natures wonders together with fresh healthy food, good company ... and of course good music...  that's the base for the recipe for my own contentment.
When you stay at Gwenn's you aren't booking a hotel, you are booking an experience!

name: Light and spacious house with sea views
description:
Light-filled and spacious architect-designed simple house for four, set amongst peaceful grassy hills and farmland with long views to the sea . Brilliant for a family or couples. Sandy beaches nearby.

Large double height, south-facing open living area with wood-burning stove. Two good sized bedrooms, one en-suite, and well-equipped kitchen.
Garden facing south to the sea.


Week long bookings only 17 July - 7 September
neighborhood_overview:
What makes this place special?

The sense of space and getting away from it all. The sea and beach nearby and the warmth and welcome of the Irish people
Things to do

Ballybrannigan Strand
This beach runs all the way from the below the house to the car park at Ballybrannigan.


Ballinrostig – the pub and music
On some evenings the pub, ‘Cor Ar Buile’ (formerly ‘Walls Bar’) in Ballinrostig has music – provided by local people who come and play together. Usually traditional Irish folk music. Highly recommended – music starts at about 10pm. Very friendly, families are welcome.

Ballycotton
Ballycotton is a small fishing village about 15 minutes from the house and with a small shop and a couple of Bars. You can drive down to the harbour to watch the fishermen or drive up through the village to the cliffs. You an also fish off the harbour here –previous guests have caught mackerel here.
There is a good cliff walk here
host_about: I live and work in Oxford in the UK having spent six years in Asia in China and Thailand. I love to travel and meet people from around the world.

Kinvara and Ballyvaughan are nearby fishing and farming villages both on the edge of Galway Bay. Both villages host farmers markets on Saturday during summer months selling local produce.

Tracht beach and Bishopsquarter beach only 20 minutes' drive from the house.

name: Rose Cottage on The Sheep's Head Peninsula + WIFI
description:
Self-catering accommodation with magnificent views of Dunmanus Bay. An ideal location to tour Sheep’s Head & Mizen peninsulas. Kilcrohane village located 3 miles away has 2 pubs, 3 restaurants, a country market shop selling local produce & a children's playground with a tennis court. Numerous beaches are located along the peninsula.
Sleeps 4 max
One Bathroom with a separate shower

Minimum: [3 NIGHT] except for [JUNE JULY AND AUGUST] WEEKLY OR LONGER
WIFI: Available - €10 weekly
neighborhood_overview: The Sheep's Head peninsula is a European Destination of Excellence, and a truly unspoilt part of Ireland's Atlantic coastline. Very scenic safe and peaceful.
host_about: I live on a farm rearing cattle and sheep. The house we rent is 30 yards away from our main house, and 3 miles from the small village of Kilcrohane. Rose Cottage has a big garden and a great sea view.I supply welcome pack tea coffee milk biscuits etc We have recently upgraded the bathroom and installed a new bathroom suite and new electric shower in the house. I am fond of gardening and with my husband grow our own vegetables which we share with our guests in the Summer. At the back of the house is a mountain which is part of the Sheeps head Walking  Route. In summer there are three tea and coffee shops, two restaurants,  and also a small country market with local produce. I am fond of dogs and allow guests to bring their dogs [two max] with them. I like to travel and have been in America a few times plus Canada and Europe. I welcome all visitors to my cottage to share their travel experiences and enjoy the beauty of the Sheep's Head peninsula.The town of Bantry is 22 miles away where you can Visit Bantry House and Gardens and have a scenic walk along the sea shore,and use the exercise machines as you go along enjoy. Every Friday there is a street market with cheeses, olives, bric a brac, fruit and veg, Artisan Food . Our house is on Wild Atlantic Way Route.  house rented 3 day minium except  JUNE   JULY and AUGUST   weekly  only  or longer. We have WIFI at cost 10 EURO per Week which can be purchased on arrival,if you are only staying 3 days no charge   .Wifi is also advailable at the local restaurants, and White House Gallery and Teashop

I'm a middle-aged lady, who loves travelling, meeting new people, playing tennis, hill-walking, cooking and eating good food, reading, gardening  and enjoying my grand-children.   I live in a quiet part of Co. Kildare, in beautiful countryside, but I love to get away to exotic locations. Last holiday was sailing and travelling in Cuba, and I have had walking holidays worldwide including China, Morocco, Spain, the smaller Canary islands, Croatia and Scotland.   I am a classics student with an Masters degree in Greek and Roman civilization.

I love my home.  My house is extremely comfortable and full of character, and my garden is, I think, very beautiful.  I would love to share both with you.  If you would care to be my guest, I can offer you a country location that is close to Dublin, but which is interesting in itself.   I am a couple of miles from the nearest villages, so my location is unsuitable if you are not driving.

As a qualified EFL (English as a foreign language) teacher, I can help you if your conversationa lEnglish needs brushing up, and I can also give you formal private tuition if you wish, although this would cost extra.   

My life motto is 'Enjoy the days.  You'll be dead long enough!'

name: Chez Shea Gypsy Wagon-
description: The wagon is a good place to escape to.  Lie in bed in the morning, read your book,  hear the birds sing, see the sun peeking over the mountain. On a fine evening, you can light a fire.  You might see a fox, you might see a deer or a hare.  One time I saw a red squirrel playing in the Oak tree.  Bring your sketch pad, your journal, your knitting.  This is a place to rest and recuperate. It’s also a good stop off for people walking the Beara Way.
neighborhood_overview: We live on the Beara Peninsula- which is an area of great scenic beauty. There is a wealth of local archaeology and some lovely walks and hikes.
host_about: My partner Ger and I live with our three children on the Beara Peninsula in Co.Kerry. We live on a small farm which has been in my family for four generations (at least!)The family trade was shoe making, and locally some of the older people still remember this place as the shoemakers house. We all like old things-and that has led us to the idea of setting up a small vintage caravan site.  We  keep Kerry bog ponies- which are a native Irish breed, donkey's, chickens, ducks, cats and dogs.  We are both very interested in local history and love to discuss this with our guests. Funnily enough, I do have a life motto, or life plan. Its quite simple-MFB which stands for 'Make Fehanaugh Beautiful.'- Fehanaugh is the name of the townland we live in, and it's quite beautiful already- but I'd like to help it along.

description: Quiet, bright, welcoming, spacious Double Room in a beautiful Penthouse Apartment just 15 minutes walk to UCD/to Dublin City Centre by tram/bus. neighborhood_overview: Milltown is one of the most popular and desired places to live in Dublin City because of its beautiful setting and the LUAS tram and bus transport links to the city centre, providing a short, accessible commute to work or university.  Every convenience is on your doorstep, including shops, a range of eateries, and health and leisure services.
host_about:
I'm from Ireland, and in the past I have lived in the USA and the UK for a number of years. I'm into sport in a big way. I am a vegan foodie. 

I love to travel but still haven't quite mastered packing light. I've been to most continental European countries, plus Argentina, Australia, Canada, Cuba, Ethiopia, Iceland, India, Morocco,  New Zealand, Norway, Sweden, The Vatican Gardens, and I've been lucky enough to have had five great US road trips, East to West, North and South, taking in nearly every US state, and there's so many more places I want to go to...   if I win the lottery (which would be difficult given that I rarely play it!) I'd go island-hopping around the world. 

I love to read a good [auto]biography. I simply can't do without family, friends, horses, dogs (all animals, really) the beach and the sun.  

My life's motto is: treat others as you would like to be treated.

name: Huge apartment in central location
description: Experienced Host, Broadband Wifi, Towels, Toiletries, Cable TV, CD, DVD, books, Intercom, maps, snacks, secure rear parking space, 24 Hour check in, on call repairs. JUST RENOVATED Exceptionally comfortable, spacious, modern and in Dublin 4, Dublin's most prestigious residential location. Easy access to city and coast by bus and train. Lots of great restaurants, pubs, park and shops within a few minutes walking distance on Baggot Street and Ballsbridge. Host available to make recommendations.
neighborhood_overview: Ballsbridge is the best neighbourhood in Dublin. There is a bus stop right outside the block which takes you to the city centre. The DART rail station is a short walk away and gives you access to the whole of Dublin's coastal villages. Baggot Street (a five minute walk) which is nearby has everything you need, a good Supermarket, Deli, pubs, restaurants, pharmacy and other shops. It's a really nice walk (20 minutes) through Georgian Dublin to the city centre and there are great restaurants and traditional Irish bars along the way. Herbert Park is a short walk away (five minutes) if you feel like relaxing and you're near Aviva Stadium if you like Sports. You're within walking distance of Sandymount Village  (ten minutes) and the beach if you feel like enjoying great views and  a walk on the beach.  the DART train station is near (five minutes) and you can take the train along the coast to lovely villages on the North or South side of Dublin.
host_about: I love living in Dublin. It's a really friendly city and a great place to bring up kids. There's always something on, a play, a movie or a new restaurant opening up. There's lots of cultural events and sports facilities nearby. I like travelling to other cites all over the world if I'm travelling without my kids. If it's a family holiday the south of Spain or Crete are great for sunshine, swimming and food.

name: Seaside Hideaway, Dún Laoghaire
description:
Welcome to our family home in the beautiful seaside setting of Dun Laoghaire.

Escape the hustle and bustle of the city centre, and take time out to be by the sea, and live like a local.

Our home is nestled between the quaint village of Monkstown and Dun Laoghaire town, down a quiet cul de sac - perfect for a weekend getaway.

We can't wait to host you and we hope you love our home as much as we do.
neighborhood_overview:
South county Dublin's most picturesque village of Monkstown is a leisurely 10 minute stroll away . Here you'll find great cafes, restaurants, small boutiques, as well as the swimming spot at Seapoint. Don't forget your swimsuit in case you are feeling brave.

Dun Laoghaire town is five minutes away. Don't miss the Sunday food and craft market (10am-4pm), as well as the famous Dun Laoghaire pier walk. Grab yourself a nice coffee on the way and take in the sights: Maritime Museum, DLR Lexicon building that boasts unparalleled views of Dublin Bay. Continuing out this direction, why not have a Teddy's ice-cream and stroll to Sandycove beach and The Forty Foot swim spot. (Still have the swimsuit?) The James Joyce museum is also here. If you're in the mood, The Pavillion theatre is worth checking out and taking in a show.

name: Ring Of Kerry Sunshine House
description: A lovely newbuilt house in a gorgeous location. Mountains all around and big south facing conservatory and garden. See the sun rise and set here in Croi Danu, and in between, enjoy all the  beautiful day trips that Kerry has to offer. Over the years, many guests have described this house as a "5 star" rental, "best ever airbnb" and other complimentary descriptions.
neighborhood_overview: The house is on the famous Ring of Kerry, with so many beaches, mountain trails, woodland walks only a short drive from here. Situated down a quiet boireen, yet very close to town - 10 minute walk - gives you the benefit of complete peace & quiet, with the option to enjoy the  pubs and restaurants a short walk away. Cromane beach is a 10 minute drive away - last summer I swam there almost every day, the water like silk on the skin. We are 20 mins from Killarney town & National Park, 25 mins from Kerry airport, 20 minutes from the expansive and wild Rossbeigh beach, where you can walk for miles or hire a horse from nearby Burke's stables.  The town of Killorglin is a friendly one, with someone always ready to help with directions. There is a library, and next door a tourist information office, where the staff are exceptionally helpful and friendly, and a couple of cafes in the plaza, to while away an hour and people watch.There are several pubs, some with live music, and some good resta
host_about:
A Killarney native, I have lived in Killorglin for just over 8 years. I have built this house and a Therapy Centre here - finished August 2013 - so that I can have a beautiful space to to live in, to share with friends and guests and to practice my therapeutic work. I lived in London for many years and then in Cork for many more, before moving back to my native Kerry. I choose this location for it's panoramic views of the mountains all around, which change hour by hour, and for it's large private garden space, which I am slowly developping. I love my work, walking in nature, reading, travel and meeting people from different cultures to share experiences. I love nature's beauties and telling people about the loveliness of Kerry. I enjoy delicious healthy food, lots of walking - especially by the sea - and a glass of good wine. I love to sing and I sing in 2 Kerry choirs. When I travel, I like independent travelling, self catering, the choice to relate or not, as the mood takes me, so I offer that to my guests too - freedom of making your own food, non-intrusive care and comfort. Do your own thing - & I'm available if you need any information, to help in any way I can to make your visit more enjoyable. While I am definitely not fluent, I can get by in French, Spanish and Italian - enough to help with everyday things, but not philosophical discussion!
  My life motto -" Life is a mystery to be lived, not a problem to be solved!"

name: 4 star home on idyllic 450 acres
description:
Photos updated October 2022!

4* rated property on idyllic 450 acre Fairymount Farm in the heart of Ireland. Newly renovated, bright and spacious w four bedrooms (two single, two double) Conservatory leading to stone built patio, bbq area and garden.
neighborhood_overview:
As mentioned, you will have full access to the walks and trails around the farm that start the second you walk out of the The Old Cottage. Peaceful area.

It really is an deal central base for touring Ireland, 2hr drive Dublin, 1hr Galway while having amenities such as four 18 hole golf courses , horse-riding, fishing, traditional pubs and century old castles within a 18 kilometer radius. Birr Heritage town with the second largest telescope in the world is also ten miles away with great pubs and restaurants.
host_about:
My wife and I live on the other side of our 450 acre farm and have been involved in self-catering for 29 years, only discovering AirBnB in the last few!

We have put our heart and soul into designing the two cottages to ensure they are clean, cosy, bright (with great views) and fully equipped with all the mod cons you need!

We are involved in farming, horse breeding, tourism. It is very important to us to conserve the natural beauty of our farm, making discrete pathways within and growing thousands of trees in the past decade, as well as preserving natural marshlands and a native ancient oakwood- one of very few remaining in Ireland!

We love welcoming new people, hearing their stories and trying to make their stay here as enjoyable as possible. We're eager to hear from you, or answer any questions you may have!

We also live on the other side of the farm and would love to meet and help you with any queries on your stay.

name: Historical Thatch Cottage@Award-Winning Cnoc Suain
description:
''A place quite unlike any other'' The Guardian.

Welcome to Cnoc Suain, our family-owned hillside settlement nestled within an enchanting rural landscape in the Gaeltacht region of Connemara.

Located on a popular cycling route between two villages:Spiddal(6.5km) for beach, crafts & music, and Moycullen(8.5km)for Friday farmers market & adventure centre. Only 25 mins drive from Galway City(Ireland's cultural capital)yet fully immersed in the wild beauty of Connemara.
neighborhood_overview:
The cottage is 6km from the coastline, on the Wild Atlantic Way. It is a 25-minute drive/20 km from Galway City (via Moycullen village), Ireland’s cultural capital.

It is located in a rural countryside setting and situated in the Conamara Gaeltacht (Irish/Gaelic speaking region) on the Mountain Road between the villages of An Spidéal (Spiddal) and Maigh Cuilinn (Moycullen). An Baile Íochtar (The Lower Village) on the property is immersed in the tranquil surrounds of Cnoc Suain’s privately owned 200-acre nature preserve.

There are neighbouring farms with cattle and sheep.

The picturesque coastal fishing village of An Spidéal (Spiddal) has two beaches and piers, a scenic coastal walk, craft village & café, pubs, restaurant, takeaways, takeaway coffee, pharmacy, medical centre and small supermarket & gas station, and is a 9-minute (6.5km) drive from Cnoc Suain.

The village of Maigh Cuilinn (Moycullen) is situated near the Corrib Lake. Artisana
host_about:
Hello, and welcome to our home, Cnoc Suain, a hillside settlement in the Connemara Gaeltacht.

My name is Dearbhaill, and I am a musician, teacher, and native Gaelic speaker from Connemara. My husband, Charlie, is a natural scientist and teacher from Dublin.

The combined passion we share for the culture and nature of Connemara has been our inspiration throughout the restoration of this settlement and experiences we offer. 

We can happily recommend places, events, activities, and experiences – both well known and lesser known – that bring you to the heart of the culture of the area. 

We have received national and international recognition for our cultural programmes, environmental stewardship, and restoration work. Awards Cnoc Suain has won include a "Global Vision Award" from Travel + Leisure magazine and a "World Ethical Travel Award" from The Guardian newspaper. After winning the Irish award for Cultural Heritage at the Irish Centre for Responsible Tourism Awards held in Dublin in March 2015, Cnoc Suain later won a world award for Cultural Heritage at the World Responsible Tourism Awards held in London in November 2015.

In 2017, Cnoc Suain was judged as Ireland's "Best Cultural Experience" by the Irish Tourism Industry Awards.

We look forward to having you stay! 

Le dea-ghuí,

Dearbhaill & Charlie

name: Deerpark Cottage, Convenient & Calm
description:
Spacious 3 bedroom, 2-bathroom cottage in immaculate condition. Comfortably sleeps 6. Three King size bedrooms, with the option to put a baby's crib in one of the rooms
Situated in Calverstown, just off the M9 motorway, near the towns of Kilcullen, Naas, & Newbridge.
neighborhood_overview:
Calverstown is a lovely quiet country village, conveniently located near the the M9 & M7, and the towns of Kilcullen, Naas and Newbridge. Also in close proximity are Kildare Outlet Village, Punchestown Racecourse, and the Curragh.
There are very good resturants within a short distance - Fallon's Bar & Restaurant with both bar and restaurant menu's. Bardon's (Gastro pub) for great low-key dining. The Brown Bear - bar & restaurant. Ballymore Inn - Bar & Restaurant. Traditional Irish music in local bars too.
The Curragh is also close by: A flat open plain of almost 5,000 acres (20 km²) of common land in County Kildare, Ireland, between Newbridge and Kildare. This area is well known for Irish horse breeding and training. Also located here is Pollardstown Fen, the largest fen in Ireland. This area is of particular interest to botanists and ecologists because of the numerous bird species that nest and visit there. There are also many rare plants that grow there.

name: Lough Graney Traditional Irish Farm Cottage
description: The beautiful County Clare lakeshore setting of this 200 year old whitewashed farm cottage is just magical in idyllic countyside. Lough Graney Cottage is an oasis where one may fish,walk,cycle .It is the original farmhouse of this farm. The magnificent setting at Lough Graney inspired  Brian Merrimans epic  poem ,The Midnight Court. Enjoy the Feakle  Irish music Festival in  August  or  Wednesday night Traditional music  sessions  in Peppers and Thursdays Shorts in Feakle 5 km away.
neighborhood_overview: This is a beautiful sylvan setting with lakes, trees, hills and valleys making up this East Clare scenery. Brian Merriman, one of Ireland's most celebrated gaelic poets  of the 18th Century, was so enthralled by the beauty of the sorroundings that the opening octet in the celebrated Midnight Court describes most beautifully The scenery at Lough Graney.Te very best place locally to take in the breathtaking scenery is by climbing the Mass Path  over the stiles,to the upper Corlea Road , just beyond O Mara's general grocery shop in Flagmount Please keep your dogs on a leash  as there are cattle in the adjoining fields.
host_about: I love hosting and meeting visitors here on our little family farm . Our traditional cottage has been in our family for well over 200 years so we are very proud to share it with our guests . We do our best to introduce to the loveliest places in EastClare, The Burren  and indeed all  of Clare, Galway  and sorrounding regions.

With excellent amenities including a large harbour with promenades, plenty of parks, the Pavillion Theatre & IMC Cinema, this historic town also benefits from shopping centres and supermarkets as well as great restaurants & bars.

name: Studio with a view over Dublin city
description:
Beautiful Victorian studio that has been refurbished to a very high standard.
Bright & spacious it can sleep 2 comfortably and has all the comforts of home with excellent public transport links.
Supermarket is 3 min walk and pubs and restaurants all within a 10 minute walk. City centre 10 min by bus with excellent service right outside front door.
WiFi, parking and all utilities included in the price and laundry facilities available.
Phoenix park 8 min walk with Dublin Zoo and bike hire
neighborhood_overview:
This street is a beautifully tree lined street which runs right up the the entrance of the Phoenix Park.
This park is the largest urban park in Europe and houses Dublin Zoo and the presidential home and offices as well as a children's playground. It is a wonderful park to visit and spans over 1750 acres.
The street also has beautiful Victorian red bricked houses all along it which date back to the 18th century so it really is a taste of old Dublin.
There is a major supermarket just 2 minutes walk as well as a pharmacy, bakery, coffee shops, bars, restuarants and many other amenities all within easy walking distance.
host_about: I grew up in the tourist business as my parents ran a hotel in Kildare so I have always wanted to get back into the hosptality industry.  I have owned this house from the early '90's when I returned from New York where I had lived for a number of years.  I have been in the buidling trade for the last 20 years so I thought I would combine the two and refurbish the house and provide rental accommodation in an extremely convenient locations to tourists.

name: Atlantic Coastal Village House
description: A welcoming, bright and warm house situated in the unique village of Allihies, on the stunning Wild Atlantic Way (WAW).  A perfect base to enjoy outdoor activities, sample the local friendliness and visit some of the wonders and secrets of the WAW.
neighborhood_overview:
Allihies is at the western tip of the Beara Peninsula. It enjoys spectacular Atlantic views and sunsets. Despite it's remoteness it has a strong mining heritage and history which adds to the uniqueness of this little known gem. The landscape is rugged and beautiful and attracts many artists and photographers. Music is a regular feature in the pubs of the village where the main draw is good company and good conversation.

The village also has a petrol station, grocery store, post office, modern mine museum with cafe and art gallery.

Situated on the Beara way this is a walkers paradise. There are many walks for the novice and experienced walkers and much to appeal to all.
